47 static SDValue stripBitcast(SDValue Val) { 0
48 return Val.getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST ? Val.getOperand(0) : Val; 0
49 } ----
50 ----
51 // Figure out if this is really an extract of the high 16-bits of a dword. ----
52 static bool isExtractHiElt(SDValue In, SDValue &Out) { 0
53 In = stripBitcast(In); 0
54 ----
55 if (In.getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT) { 0
56 if (ConstantSDNode *Idx = dyn_cast(In.getOperand(1))) { 0
57 if (!Idx->isOne()) 0
58 return false; 0
59 Out = In.getOperand(0); 0
60 return true; 0
61 } ----
62 } ----
63 ----
64 if (In.getOpcode() != ISD::TRUNCATE) 0
65 return false; 0
66 ----
67 SDValue Srl = In.getOperand(0); 0
68 if (Srl.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL) { 0
69 if (ConstantSDNode *ShiftAmt = dyn_cast(Srl.getOperand(1))) { 0
70 if (ShiftAmt->getZExtValue() == 16) { 0
71 Out = stripBitcast(Srl.getOperand(0)); 0
72 return true; 0
73 } ----
74 } ----
75 } ----
76 ----
77 return false; 0
78 } ----
79 ----
80 // Look through operations that obscure just looking at the low 16-bits of the ----
81 // same register. ----
82 static SDValue stripExtractLoElt(SDValue In) { 0
83 if (In.getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT) { 0
84 if (ConstantSDNode *Idx = dyn_cast(In.getOperand(1))) { 0
85 if (Idx->isZero() && In.getValueSizeInBits() <= 32) 0
86 return In.getOperand(0); 0
87 } ----
88 } ----
89 ----
90 if (In.getOpcode() == ISD::TRUNCATE) { 0
91 SDValue Src = In.getOperand(0); 0
92 if (Src.getValueType().getSizeInBits() == 32) 0
93 return stripBitcast(Src); 0
94 } ----
95 ----
96 return In; 0
97 } ----
98 ----
99 } // end anonymous namespace ----

139 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::fp16SrcZerosHighBits(unsigned Opc) const { 0
140 // XXX - only need to list legal operations. ----
141 switch (Opc) { 0
142 case ISD::FADD: 0
143 case ISD::FSUB: ----
144 case ISD::FMUL: ----
145 case ISD::FDIV: ----
146 case ISD::FREM: ----
147 case ISD::FCANONICALIZE: ----
148 case ISD::UINT_TO_FP: ----
149 case ISD::SINT_TO_FP: ----
150 case ISD::FABS: ----
151 // Fabs is lowered to a bit operation, but it's an and which will clear the ----
152 // high bits anyway. ----
153 case ISD::FSQRT: ----
154 case ISD::FSIN: ----
155 case ISD::FCOS: ----
156 case ISD::FPOWI: ----
157 case ISD::FPOW: ----
158 case ISD::FLOG: ----
159 case ISD::FLOG2: ----
160 case ISD::FLOG10: ----
161 case ISD::FEXP: ----
162 case ISD::FEXP2: ----
163 case ISD::FCEIL: ----
164 case ISD::FTRUNC: ----
165 case ISD::FRINT: ----
166 case ISD::FNEARBYINT: ----
167 case ISD::FROUND: ----
168 case ISD::FFLOOR: ----
169 case ISD::FMINNUM: ----
170 case ISD::FMAXNUM: ----
171 case ISD::FLDEXP: ----
172 case AMDGPUISD::FRACT: ----
173 case AMDGPUISD::CLAMP: ----
174 case AMDGPUISD::COS_HW: ----
175 case AMDGPUISD::SIN_HW: ----
176 case AMDGPUISD::FMIN3: ----
177 case AMDGPUISD::FMAX3: ----
178 case AMDGPUISD::FMED3: ----
179 case AMDGPUISD::FMAD_FTZ: ----
180 case AMDGPUISD::RCP: ----
181 case AMDGPUISD::RSQ: ----
182 case AMDGPUISD::RCP_IFLAG: ----
183 // On gfx10, all 16-bit instructions preserve the high bits. ----
184 return Subtarget->getGeneration() <= AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX9; 0
185 case ISD::FP_ROUND: 0
186 // We may select fptrunc (fma/mad) to mad_mixlo, which does not zero the ----
187 // high bits on gfx9. ----
188 // TODO: If we had the source node we could see if the source was fma/mad ----
189 return Subtarget->getGeneration() == AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS; 0
190 case ISD::FMA: 0
191 case ISD::FMAD: ----
192 case AMDGPUISD::DIV_FIXUP: ----
193 return Subtarget->getGeneration() == AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS; 0
194 default: 0
195 // fcopysign, select and others may be lowered to 32-bit bit operations ----
196 // which don't zero the high bits. ----
197 return false; 0
198 } ----

211 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::matchLoadD16FromBuildVector(SDNode *N) const { 0
212 assert(Subtarget->d16PreservesUnusedBits()); 0
213 MVT VT = N->getValueType(0).getSimpleVT(); 0
214 if (VT != MVT::v2i16 && VT != MVT::v2f16) 0
215 return false; 0
216 ----
217 SDValue Lo = N->getOperand(0); 0
218 SDValue Hi = N->getOperand(1); 0
219 ----
220 LoadSDNode *LdHi = dyn_cast(stripBitcast(Hi)); 0
221 ----
222 // build_vector lo, (load ptr) -> load_d16_hi ptr, lo ----
223 // build_vector lo, (zextload ptr from i8) -> load_d16_hi_u8 ptr, lo ----
224 // build_vector lo, (sextload ptr from i8) -> load_d16_hi_i8 ptr, lo ----
225 ----
226 // Need to check for possible indirect dependencies on the other half of the ----
227 // vector to avoid introducing a cycle. ----
228 if (LdHi && Hi.hasOneUse() && !LdHi->isPredecessorOf(Lo.getNode())) { 0
229 SDVTList VTList = CurDAG->getVTList(VT, MVT::Other); 0
230 ----
231 SDValue TiedIn = CurDAG->getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, SDLoc(N), VT, Lo); 0
232 SDValue Ops[] = { ----
233 LdHi->getChain(), LdHi->getBasePtr(), TiedIn 0
234 }; 0
235 ----
236 unsigned LoadOp = AMDGPUISD::LOAD_D16_HI; 0
237 if (LdHi->getMemoryVT() == MVT::i8) { 0
238 LoadOp = LdHi->getExtensionType() == ISD::SEXTLOAD ? 0
239 AMDGPUISD::LOAD_D16_HI_I8 : AMDGPUISD::LOAD_D16_HI_U8; ----
240 } else { ----
241 assert(LdHi->getMemoryVT() == MVT::i16); 0
242 } ----
243 ----
244 SDValue NewLoadHi = ----
245 CurDAG->getMemIntrinsicNode(LoadOp, SDLoc(LdHi), VTList, 0
246 Ops, LdHi->getMemoryVT(), ----
247 LdHi->getMemOperand()); ----
248 ----
249 CurDAG->ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), NewLoadHi); 0
250 CurDAG->ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(LdHi, 1), NewLoadHi.getValue(1)); 0
251 return true; 0
252 } ----
253 ----
254 // build_vector (load ptr), hi -> load_d16_lo ptr, hi ----
255 // build_vector (zextload ptr from i8), hi -> load_d16_lo_u8 ptr, hi ----
256 // build_vector (sextload ptr from i8), hi -> load_d16_lo_i8 ptr, hi ----
257 LoadSDNode *LdLo = dyn_cast(stripBitcast(Lo)); 0
258 if (LdLo && Lo.hasOneUse()) { 0
259 SDValue TiedIn = getHi16Elt(Hi); 0
260 if (!TiedIn || LdLo->isPredecessorOf(TiedIn.getNode())) 0
261 return false; 0
262 ----
263 SDVTList VTList = CurDAG->getVTList(VT, MVT::Other); 0
264 unsigned LoadOp = AMDGPUISD::LOAD_D16_LO; 0
265 if (LdLo->getMemoryVT() == MVT::i8) { 0
266 LoadOp = LdLo->getExtensionType() == ISD::SEXTLOAD ? 0
267 AMDGPUISD::LOAD_D16_LO_I8 : AMDGPUISD::LOAD_D16_LO_U8; ----
268 } else { ----
269 assert(LdLo->getMemoryVT() == MVT::i16); 0
270 } ----
271 ----
272 TiedIn = CurDAG->getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SDLoc(N), VT, TiedIn); 0
273 ----
274 SDValue Ops[] = { ----
275 LdLo->getChain(), LdLo->getBasePtr(), TiedIn 0
276 }; 0
277 ----
278 SDValue NewLoadLo = ----
279 CurDAG->getMemIntrinsicNode(LoadOp, SDLoc(LdLo), VTList, 0
280 Ops, LdLo->getMemoryVT(), ----
281 LdLo->getMemOperand()); ----
282 ----
283 CurDAG->ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), NewLoadLo); 0
284 CurDAG->ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(LdLo, 1), NewLoadLo.getValue(1)); 0
285 return true; 0
286 } ----
287 ----
288 return false; 0
289 } ----

291 void AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::PreprocessISelDAG() { 0
292 if (!Subtarget->d16PreservesUnusedBits()) 0
293 return; 0
294 ----
295 SelectionDAG::allnodes_iterator Position = CurDAG->allnodes_end(); 0
296 ----
297 bool MadeChange = false; 0
298 while (Position != CurDAG->allnodes_begin()) { 0
299 SDNode *N = &*--Position; 0
300 if (N->use_empty()) 0
301 continue; 0
302 ----
303 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
304 case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: 0
305 MadeChange |= matchLoadD16FromBuildVector(N); 0
306 break; 0
307 default: 0
308 break; 0
309 } ----
310 } ----
311 ----
312 if (MadeChange) { 0
313 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNodes(); 0
314 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "After PreProcess:\n"; 0
315 CurDAG->dump();); ----
316 } ----
317 } ----

319 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::isInlineImmediate(const SDNode *N, 0
320 bool Negated) const { ----
321 if (N->isUndef()) 0
322 return true; 0
323 ----
324 const SIInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget->getInstrInfo(); 0
325 if (Negated) { 0
326 if (const ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(N)) 0
327 return TII->isInlineConstant(-C->getAPIntValue()); 0
328 ----
329 if (const ConstantFPSDNode *C = dyn_cast(N)) 0
330 return TII->isInlineConstant(-C->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt()); 0
331 ----
332 } else { ----
333 if (const ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(N)) 0
334 return TII->isInlineConstant(C->getAPIntValue()); 0
335 ----
336 if (const ConstantFPSDNode *C = dyn_cast(N)) 0
337 return TII->isInlineConstant(C->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt()); 0
338 } ----
339 ----
340 return false; 0
341 } ----

343 /// Determine the register class for \p OpNo ----
344 /// \returns The register class of the virtual register that will be used for ----
345 /// the given operand number \OpNo or NULL if the register class cannot be ----
346 /// determined. ----
347 const TargetRegisterClass *AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::getOperandRegClass(SDNode *N, 0
348 unsigned OpNo) const { ----
349 if (!N->isMachineOpcode()) { 0
350 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::CopyToReg) { 0
351 Register Reg = cast(N->getOperand(1))->getReg(); 0
352 if (Reg.isVirtual()) { 0
353 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = CurDAG->getMachineFunction().getRegInfo(); 0
354 return MRI.getRegClass(Reg); 0
355 } ----
356 ----
357 const SIRegisterInfo *TRI ----
358 = static_cast(Subtarget)->getRegisterInfo(); 0
359 return TRI->getPhysRegBaseClass(Reg); 0
360 } ----
361 ----
362 return nullptr; 0
363 } ----
364 ----
365 switch (N->getMachineOpcode()) { 0
366 default: { 0
367 const MCInstrDesc &Desc = ----
368 Subtarget->getInstrInfo()->get(N->getMachineOpcode()); 0
369 unsigned OpIdx = Desc.getNumDefs() + OpNo; 0
370 if (OpIdx >= Desc.getNumOperands()) 0
371 return nullptr; 0
372 int RegClass = Desc.operands()[OpIdx].RegClass; 0
373 if (RegClass == -1) 0
374 return nullptr; 0
375 ----
376 return Subtarget->getRegisterInfo()->getRegClass(RegClass); 0
377 } ----
378 case AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE: { 0
379 unsigned RCID = cast(N->getOperand(0))->getZExtValue(); 0
380 const TargetRegisterClass *SuperRC = ----
381 Subtarget->getRegisterInfo()->getRegClass(RCID); 0
382 ----
383 SDValue SubRegOp = N->getOperand(OpNo + 1); 0
384 unsigned SubRegIdx = cast(SubRegOp)->getZExtValue(); 0
385 return Subtarget->getRegisterInfo()->getSubClassWithSubReg(SuperRC, 0
386 SubRegIdx); 0
387 } ----
388 } ----
389 } ----

391 SDNode *AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::glueCopyToOp(SDNode *N, SDValue NewChain, 0
392 SDValue Glue) const { ----
393 SmallVector Ops; 0
394 Ops.push_back(NewChain); // Replace the chain. 0
395 for (unsigned i = 1, e = N->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) 0
396 Ops.push_back(N->getOperand(i)); 0
397 ----
398 Ops.push_back(Glue); 0
399 return CurDAG->MorphNodeTo(N, N->getOpcode(), N->getVTList(), Ops); 0
400 } 0

427 EVT VT) const { ----

442 void AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectBuildVector(SDNode *N, unsigned RegClassID) { 0
443 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0); 0
444 unsigned NumVectorElts = VT.getVectorNumElements(); 0
445 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType(); 0
446 SDLoc DL(N); 0
447 SDValue RegClass = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RegClassID, DL, MVT::i32); 0
448 ----
449 if (NumVectorElts == 1) { 0
450 CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, AMDGPU::COPY_TO_REGCLASS, EltVT, N->getOperand(0), 0
451 RegClass); ----
452 return; 0
453 } ----
454 ----
455 assert(NumVectorElts <= 32 && "Vectors with more than 32 elements not " 0
456 "supported yet"); ----
457 // 32 = Max Num Vector Elements ----
458 // 2 = 2 REG_SEQUENCE operands per element (value, subreg index) ----
459 // 1 = Vector Register Class ----
460 SmallVector RegSeqArgs(NumVectorElts * 2 + 1); 0
461 ----
462 bool IsGCN = CurDAG->getSubtarget().getTargetTriple().getArch() == 0
463 Triple::amdgcn; 0
464 RegSeqArgs[0] = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RegClassID, DL, MVT::i32); 0
465 bool IsRegSeq = true; 0
466 unsigned NOps = N->getNumOperands(); 0
467 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NOps; i++) { 0
468 // XXX: Why is this here? ----
469 if (isa(N->getOperand(i))) { 0
470 IsRegSeq = false; 0
471 break; 0
472 } ----
473 unsigned Sub = IsGCN ? SIRegisterInfo::getSubRegFromChannel(i) 0
474 : R600RegisterInfo::getSubRegFromChannel(i); 0
475 RegSeqArgs[1 + (2 * i)] = N->getOperand(i); 0
476 RegSeqArgs[1 + (2 * i) + 1] = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Sub, DL, MVT::i32); 0
477 } ----
478 if (NOps != NumVectorElts) { 0
479 // Fill in the missing undef elements if this was a scalar_to_vector. ----
480 assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR && NOps < NumVectorElts); 0
481 MachineSDNode *ImpDef = CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::IMPLICIT_DEF, 0
482 DL, EltVT); ----
483 for (unsigned i = NOps; i < NumVectorElts; ++i) { 0
484 unsigned Sub = IsGCN ? SIRegisterInfo::getSubRegFromChannel(i) 0
485 : R600RegisterInfo::getSubRegFromChannel(i); 0
486 RegSeqArgs[1 + (2 * i)] = SDValue(ImpDef, 0); 0
487 RegSeqArgs[1 + (2 * i) + 1] = 0
488 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Sub, DL, MVT::i32); 0
489 } ----
490 } ----
491 ----
492 if (!IsRegSeq) 0
493 SelectCode(N); 0
494 CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE, N->getVTList(), RegSeqArgs); 0
495 } 0
496 ----
497 void AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::Select(SDNode *N) { 0
498 unsigned int Opc = N->getOpcode(); 0
499 if (N->isMachineOpcode()) { 0
500 N->setNodeId(-1); 0
501 return; // Already selected. 0
502 } ----
503 ----
504 // isa almost works but is slightly too permissive for some DS ----
505 // intrinsics. ----
506 if (Opc == ISD::LOAD || Opc == ISD::STORE || isa(N) || 0
507 Opc == AMDGPUISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_FMIN || 0
508 Opc == AMDGPUISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_FMAX) { ----
509 N = glueCopyToM0LDSInit(N); 0
510 SelectCode(N); 0
511 return; 0
512 } ----
513 ----
514 switch (Opc) { 0
515 default: 0
516 break; 0
517 // We are selecting i64 ADD here instead of custom lower it during ----
518 // DAG legalization, so we can fold some i64 ADDs used for address ----
519 // calculation into the LOAD and STORE instructions. ----
520 case ISD::ADDC: 0
521 case ISD::ADDE: ----
522 case ISD::SUBC: ----
523 case ISD::SUBE: { ----
524 if (N->getValueType(0) != MVT::i64) 0
525 break; 0
526 ----
527 SelectADD_SUB_I64(N); 0
528 return; 0
529 } ----
530 case ISD::UADDO_CARRY: 0
531 case ISD::USUBO_CARRY: ----
532 if (N->getValueType(0) != MVT::i32) 0
533 break; 0
534 ----
535 SelectAddcSubb(N); 0
536 return; 0
537 case ISD::UADDO: 0
538 case ISD::USUBO: { ----
539 SelectUADDO_USUBO(N); 0
540 return; 0
541 } ----
542 case AMDGPUISD::FMUL_W_CHAIN: { 0
543 SelectFMUL_W_CHAIN(N); 0
544 return; 0
545 } ----
546 case AMDGPUISD::FMA_W_CHAIN: { 0
547 SelectFMA_W_CHAIN(N); 0
548 return; 0
549 } ----
550 ----
551 case ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR: 0
552 case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: { ----
553 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0); 0
554 unsigned NumVectorElts = VT.getVectorNumElements(); 0
555 if (VT.getScalarSizeInBits() == 16) { 0
556 if (Opc == ISD::BUILD_VECTOR && NumVectorElts == 2) { 0
557 if (SDNode *Packed = packConstantV2I16(N, *CurDAG)) { 0
558 ReplaceNode(N, Packed); 0
559 return; 0
560 } ----
561 } ----
562 ----
563 break; 0
564 } ----
565 ----
566 assert(VT.getVectorElementType().bitsEq(MVT::i32)); 0
567 unsigned RegClassID = ----
568 SIRegisterInfo::getSGPRClassForBitWidth(NumVectorElts * 32)->getID(); 0
569 SelectBuildVector(N, RegClassID); 0
570 return; 0
571 } ----
572 case ISD::BUILD_PAIR: { 0
573 SDValue RC, SubReg0, SubReg1; 0
574 SDLoc DL(N); 0
575 if (N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i128) { 0
576 RC = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::SGPR_128RegClassID, DL, MVT::i32); 0
577 SubReg0 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub0_sub1, DL, MVT::i32); 0
578 SubReg1 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub2_sub3, DL, MVT::i32); 0
579 } else if (N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i64) { 0
580 RC = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClassID, DL, MVT::i32); 0
581 SubReg0 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
582 SubReg1 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub1, DL, MVT::i32); 0
583 } else { ----
584 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled value type for BUILD_PAIR"); 0
585 } ----
586 const SDValue Ops[] = { RC, N->getOperand(0), SubReg0, 0
587 N->getOperand(1), SubReg1 }; 0
588 ReplaceNode(N, CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE, DL, 0
589 N->getValueType(0), Ops)); ----
590 return; 0
591 } 0
592 ----
593 case ISD::Constant: 0
594 case ISD::ConstantFP: { ----
595 if (N->getValueType(0).getSizeInBits() != 64 || isInlineImmediate(N)) 0
596 break; 0
597 ----
598 uint64_t Imm; ----
599 if (ConstantFPSDNode *FP = dyn_cast(N)) 0
600 Imm = FP->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue(); 0
601 else { ----
602 ConstantSDNode *C = cast(N); 0
603 Imm = C->getZExtValue(); 0
604 } ----
605 ----
606 SDLoc DL(N); 0
607 ReplaceNode(N, buildSMovImm64(DL, Imm, N->getValueType(0))); 0
608 return; 0
609 } 0
610 case AMDGPUISD::BFE_I32: 0
611 case AMDGPUISD::BFE_U32: { ----
612 // There is a scalar version available, but unlike the vector version which ----
613 // has a separate operand for the offset and width, the scalar version packs ----
614 // the width and offset into a single operand. Try to move to the scalar ----
615 // version if the offsets are constant, so that we can try to keep extended ----
616 // loads of kernel arguments in SGPRs. ----
617 ----
618 // TODO: Technically we could try to pattern match scalar bitshifts of ----
619 // dynamic values, but it's probably not useful. ----
620 ConstantSDNode *Offset = dyn_cast(N->getOperand(1)); 0
621 if (!Offset) 0
622 break; 0
623 ----
624 ConstantSDNode *Width = dyn_cast(N->getOperand(2)); 0
625 if (!Width) 0
626 break; 0
627 ----
628 bool Signed = Opc == AMDGPUISD::BFE_I32; 0
629 ----
630 uint32_t OffsetVal = Offset->getZExtValue(); 0
631 uint32_t WidthVal = Width->getZExtValue(); 0
632 ----
633 ReplaceNode(N, getBFE32(Signed, SDLoc(N), N->getOperand(0), OffsetVal, 0
634 WidthVal)); ----
635 return; 0
636 } ----
637 case AMDGPUISD::DIV_SCALE: { 0
638 SelectDIV_SCALE(N); 0
639 return; 0
640 } ----
641 case AMDGPUISD::MAD_I64_I32: 0
642 case AMDGPUISD::MAD_U64_U32: { ----
643 SelectMAD_64_32(N); 0
644 return; 0
645 } ----
646 case ISD::SMUL_LOHI: 0
647 case ISD::UMUL_LOHI: ----
648 return SelectMUL_LOHI(N); 0
649 case ISD::CopyToReg: { 0
650 const SITargetLowering& Lowering = ----
651 *static_cast(getTargetLowering()); 0
652 N = Lowering.legalizeTargetIndependentNode(N, *CurDAG); 0
653 break; 0
654 } ----
655 case ISD::AND: 0
656 case ISD::SRL: ----
657 case ISD::SRA: ----
658 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG: ----
659 if (N->getValueType(0) != MVT::i32) 0
660 break; 0
661 ----
662 SelectS_BFE(N); 0
663 return; 0
664 case ISD::BRCOND: 0
665 SelectBRCOND(N); 0
666 return; 0
667 case AMDGPUISD::CVT_PKRTZ_F16_F32: 0
668 case AMDGPUISD::CVT_PKNORM_I16_F32: ----
669 case AMDGPUISD::CVT_PKNORM_U16_F32: ----
670 case AMDGPUISD::CVT_PK_U16_U32: ----
671 case AMDGPUISD::CVT_PK_I16_I32: { ----
672 // Hack around using a legal type if f16 is illegal. ----
673 if (N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i32) { 0
674 MVT NewVT = Opc == AMDGPUISD::CVT_PKRTZ_F16_F32 ? MVT::v2f16 : MVT::v2i16; 0
675 N = CurDAG->MorphNodeTo(N, N->getOpcode(), CurDAG->getVTList(NewVT), 0
676 { N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1) }); 0
677 SelectCode(N); 0
678 return; 0
679 } ----
680 ----
681 break; 0
682 } ----
683 case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN: { 0
684 SelectINTRINSIC_W_CHAIN(N); 0
685 return; 0
686 } ----
687 case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN: { 0
688 SelectINTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN(N); 0
689 return; 0
690 } ----
691 case ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID: { 0
692 SelectINTRINSIC_VOID(N); 0
693 return; 0
694 } ----
695 } ----
696 ----
697 SelectCode(N); 0
698 } ----
699 ----
700 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::isUniformBr(const SDNode *N) const { 0
701 const BasicBlock *BB = FuncInfo->MBB->getBasicBlock(); 0
702 const Instruction *Term = BB->getTerminator(); 0
703 return Term->getMetadata("amdgpu.uniform") || 0
704 Term->getMetadata("structurizecfg.uniform"); 0
705 } ----
706 ----
707 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::isUnneededShiftMask(const SDNode *N, 0
708 unsigned ShAmtBits) const { ----
709 assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::AND); 0
710 ----
711 const APInt &RHS = cast(N->getOperand(1))->getAPIntValue(); 0
712 if (RHS.countr_one() >= ShAmtBits) 0
713 return true; 0
714 ----
715 const APInt &LHSKnownZeros = CurDAG->computeKnownBits(N->getOperand(0)).Zero; 0
716 return (LHSKnownZeros | RHS).countr_one() >= ShAmtBits; 0
717 } 0
718 ----
719 static bool getBaseWithOffsetUsingSplitOR(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Addr, 0
720 SDValue &N0, SDValue &N1) { ----
721 if (Addr.getValueType() == MVT::i64 && Addr.getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST && 0
722 Addr.getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::BUILD_VECTOR) { 0
723 // As we split 64-bit `or` earlier, it's complicated pattern to match, i.e. ----
724 // (i64 (bitcast (v2i32 (build_vector ----
725 // (or (extract_vector_elt V, 0), OFFSET), ----
726 // (extract_vector_elt V, 1))))) ----
727 SDValue Lo = Addr.getOperand(0).getOperand(0); 0
728 if (Lo.getOpcode() == ISD::OR && DAG.isBaseWithConstantOffset(Lo)) { 0
729 SDValue BaseLo = Lo.getOperand(0); 0
730 SDValue BaseHi = Addr.getOperand(0).getOperand(1); 0
731 // Check that split base (Lo and Hi) are extracted from the same one. ----
732 if (BaseLo.getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT && 0
733 BaseHi.getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT && 0
734 BaseLo.getOperand(0) == BaseHi.getOperand(0) && 0
735 // Lo is statically extracted from index 0. ----
736 isa(BaseLo.getOperand(1)) && 0
737 BaseLo.getConstantOperandVal(1) == 0 && 0
738 // Hi is statically extracted from index 0. ----
739 isa(BaseHi.getOperand(1)) && 0
740 BaseHi.getConstantOperandVal(1) == 1) { 0
741 N0 = BaseLo.getOperand(0).getOperand(0); 0
742 N1 = Lo.getOperand(1); 0
743 return true; 0
744 } ----
745 } ----
746 } ----
747 return false; 0
748 } ----
749 ----
750 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::isBaseWithConstantOffset64(SDValue Addr, SDValue &LHS, 0
751 SDValue &RHS) const { ----
752 if (CurDAG->isBaseWithConstantOffset(Addr)) { 0
753 LHS = Addr.getOperand(0); 0
754 RHS = Addr.getOperand(1); 0
755 return true; 0
756 } ----
757 ----
758 if (getBaseWithOffsetUsingSplitOR(*CurDAG, Addr, LHS, RHS)) { 0
759 assert(LHS && RHS && isa(RHS)); 0
760 return true; 0
761 } ----
762 ----
763 return false; 0
764 } ----

766 StringRef AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::getPassName() const { 0
767 return "AMDGPU DAG->DAG Pattern Instruction Selection"; 0
768 } ----

778 ----
779 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectADDRIndirect(SDValue Addr, SDValue &Base, 0
780 SDValue &Offset) { ----
781 ConstantSDNode *C; ----
782 SDLoc DL(Addr); 0
783 ----
784 if ((C = dyn_cast(Addr))) { 0
785 Base = CurDAG->getRegister(R600::INDIRECT_BASE_ADDR, MVT::i32); 0
786 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(C->getZExtValue(), DL, MVT::i32); 0
787 } else if ((Addr.getOpcode() == AMDGPUISD::DWORDADDR) && 0
788 (C = dyn_cast(Addr.getOperand(0)))) { 0
789 Base = CurDAG->getRegister(R600::INDIRECT_BASE_ADDR, MVT::i32); 0
790 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(C->getZExtValue(), DL, MVT::i32); 0
791 } else if ((Addr.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD || Addr.getOpcode() == ISD::OR) && 0
792 (C = dyn_cast(Addr.getOperand(1)))) { 0
793 Base = Addr.getOperand(0); 0
794 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(C->getZExtValue(), DL, MVT::i32); 0
795 } else { ----
796 Base = Addr; 0
797 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
798 } ----
799 ----
800 return true; 0
801 } 0
802 ----
803 SDValue AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::getMaterializedScalarImm32(int64_t Val, 0
804 const SDLoc &DL) const { ----
805 SDNode *Mov = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
806 AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32, DL, MVT::i32, ----
807 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Val, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
808 return SDValue(Mov, 0); 0
809 } ----

811 // FIXME: Should only handle uaddo_carry/usubo_carry ----
812 void AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectADD_SUB_I64(SDNode *N) { 0
813 SDLoc DL(N); 0
814 SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0); 0
815 SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1); 0
816 ----
817 unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode(); 0
818 bool ConsumeCarry = (Opcode == ISD::ADDE || Opcode == ISD::SUBE); 0
819 bool ProduceCarry = 0
820 ConsumeCarry || Opcode == ISD::ADDC || Opcode == ISD::SUBC; 0
821 bool IsAdd = Opcode == ISD::ADD || Opcode == ISD::ADDC || Opcode == ISD::ADDE; 0
822 ----
823 SDValue Sub0 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
824 SDValue Sub1 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub1, DL, MVT::i32); 0
825 ----
826 SDNode *Lo0 = CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::EXTRACT_SUBREG, 0
827 DL, MVT::i32, LHS, Sub0); ----
828 SDNode *Hi0 = CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::EXTRACT_SUBREG, 0
829 DL, MVT::i32, LHS, Sub1); ----
830 ----
831 SDNode *Lo1 = CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::EXTRACT_SUBREG, 0
832 DL, MVT::i32, RHS, Sub0); ----
833 SDNode *Hi1 = CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::EXTRACT_SUBREG, 0
834 DL, MVT::i32, RHS, Sub1); ----
835 ----
836 SDVTList VTList = CurDAG->getVTList(MVT::i32, MVT::Glue); 0
837 ----
838 static const unsigned OpcMap[2][2][2] = { ----
839 {{AMDGPU::S_SUB_U32, AMDGPU::S_ADD_U32}, ----
840 {AMDGPU::V_SUB_CO_U32_e32, AMDGPU::V_ADD_CO_U32_e32}}, ----
841 {{AMDGPU::S_SUBB_U32, AMDGPU::S_ADDC_U32}, ----
842 {AMDGPU::V_SUBB_U32_e32, AMDGPU::V_ADDC_U32_e32}}}; ----
843 ----
844 unsigned Opc = OpcMap[0][N->isDivergent()][IsAdd]; 0
845 unsigned CarryOpc = OpcMap[1][N->isDivergent()][IsAdd]; 0
846 ----
847 SDNode *AddLo; ----
848 if (!ConsumeCarry) { 0
849 SDValue Args[] = { SDValue(Lo0, 0), SDValue(Lo1, 0) }; 0
850 AddLo = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, DL, VTList, Args); 0
851 } else { ----
852 SDValue Args[] = { SDValue(Lo0, 0), SDValue(Lo1, 0), N->getOperand(2) }; 0
853 AddLo = CurDAG->getMachineNode(CarryOpc, DL, VTList, Args); 0
854 } ----
855 SDValue AddHiArgs[] = { ----
856 SDValue(Hi0, 0), ----
857 SDValue(Hi1, 0), ----
858 SDValue(AddLo, 1) ----
859 }; 0
860 SDNode *AddHi = CurDAG->getMachineNode(CarryOpc, DL, VTList, AddHiArgs); 0
861 ----
862 SDValue RegSequenceArgs[] = { ----
863 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClassID, DL, MVT::i32), 0
864 SDValue(AddLo,0), ----
865 Sub0, ----
866 SDValue(AddHi,0), ----
867 Sub1, ----
868 }; 0
869 SDNode *RegSequence = CurDAG->getMachineNode(AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE, DL, 0
870 MVT::i64, RegSequenceArgs); ----
871 ----
872 if (ProduceCarry) { 0
873 // Replace the carry-use ----
874 ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, 1), SDValue(AddHi, 1)); 0
875 } ----
876 ----
877 // Replace the remaining uses. ----
878 ReplaceNode(N, RegSequence); 0
879 } 0
880 ----
881 void AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectAddcSubb(SDNode *N) { 0
882 SDLoc DL(N); 0
883 SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0); 0
884 SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1); 0
885 SDValue CI = N->getOperand(2); 0
886 ----
887 if (N->isDivergent()) { 0
888 unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode() == ISD::UADDO_CARRY ? AMDGPU::V_ADDC_U32_e64 0
889 : AMDGPU::V_SUBB_U32_e64; 0
890 CurDAG->SelectNodeTo( 0
891 N, Opc, N->getVTList(), ----
892 {LHS, RHS, CI, ----
893 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, {}, MVT::i1) /*clamp bit*/}); 0
894 } else { ----
895 unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode() == ISD::UADDO_CARRY ? AMDGPU::S_ADD_CO_PSEUDO 0
896 : AMDGPU::S_SUB_CO_PSEUDO; 0
897 CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, Opc, N->getVTList(), {LHS, RHS, CI}); 0
898 } ----
899 } 0
900 ----
901 void AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectUADDO_USUBO(SDNode *N) { 0
902 // The name of the opcodes are misleading. v_add_i32/v_sub_i32 have unsigned ----
903 // carry out despite the _i32 name. These were renamed in VI to _U32. ----
904 // FIXME: We should probably rename the opcodes here. ----
905 bool IsAdd = N->getOpcode() == ISD::UADDO; 0
906 bool IsVALU = N->isDivergent(); 0
907 ----
908 for (SDNode::use_iterator UI = N->use_begin(), E = N->use_end(); UI != E; 0
909 ++UI) 0
910 if (UI.getUse().getResNo() == 1) { 0
911 if ((IsAdd && (UI->getOpcode() != ISD::UADDO_CARRY)) || 0
912 (!IsAdd && (UI->getOpcode() != ISD::USUBO_CARRY))) { 0
913 IsVALU = true; 0
914 break; 0
915 } ----
916 } ----
917 ----
918 if (IsVALU) { 0
919 unsigned Opc = IsAdd ? AMDGPU::V_ADD_CO_U32_e64 : AMDGPU::V_SUB_CO_U32_e64; 0
920 ----
921 CurDAG->SelectNodeTo( 0
922 N, Opc, N->getVTList(), ----
923 {N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1), 0
924 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, {}, MVT::i1) /*clamp bit*/}); 0
925 } else { ----
926 unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode() == ISD::UADDO ? AMDGPU::S_UADDO_PSEUDO 0
927 : AMDGPU::S_USUBO_PSEUDO; 0
928 ----
929 CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, Opc, N->getVTList(), 0
930 {N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1)}); 0
931 } ----
932 } 0
933 ----
934 void AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectFMA_W_CHAIN(SDNode *N) { 0
935 SDLoc SL(N); 0
936 // src0_modifiers, src0, src1_modifiers, src1, src2_modifiers, src2, clamp, omod ----
937 SDValue Ops[10]; 0
938 ----
939 SelectVOP3Mods0(N->getOperand(1), Ops[1], Ops[0], Ops[6], Ops[7]); 0
940 SelectVOP3Mods(N->getOperand(2), Ops[3], Ops[2]); 0
941 SelectVOP3Mods(N->getOperand(3), Ops[5], Ops[4]); 0
942 Ops[8] = N->getOperand(0); 0
943 Ops[9] = N->getOperand(4); 0
944 ----
945 // If there are no source modifiers, prefer fmac over fma because it can use ----
946 // the smaller VOP2 encoding. ----
947 bool UseFMAC = Subtarget->hasDLInsts() && 0
948 cast(Ops[0])->isZero() && 0
949 cast(Ops[2])->isZero() && 0
950 cast(Ops[4])->isZero(); 0
951 unsigned Opcode = UseFMAC ? AMDGPU::V_FMAC_F32_e64 : AMDGPU::V_FMA_F32_e64; 0
952 CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, Opcode, N->getVTList(), Ops); 0
953 } 0
954 ----
955 void AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectFMUL_W_CHAIN(SDNode *N) { 0
956 SDLoc SL(N); 0
957 // src0_modifiers, src0, src1_modifiers, src1, clamp, omod ----
958 SDValue Ops[8]; 0
959 ----
960 SelectVOP3Mods0(N->getOperand(1), Ops[1], Ops[0], Ops[4], Ops[5]); 0
961 SelectVOP3Mods(N->getOperand(2), Ops[3], Ops[2]); 0
962 Ops[6] = N->getOperand(0); 0
963 Ops[7] = N->getOperand(3); 0
964 ----
965 CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, AMDGPU::V_MUL_F32_e64, N->getVTList(), Ops); 0
966 } 0
967 ----
968 // We need to handle this here because tablegen doesn't support matching ----
969 // instructions with multiple outputs. ----
970 void AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectDIV_SCALE(SDNode *N) { 0
971 SDLoc SL(N); 0
972 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0); 0
973 ----
974 assert(VT == MVT::f32 || VT == MVT::f64); 0
975 ----
976 unsigned Opc ----
977 = (VT == MVT::f64) ? AMDGPU::V_DIV_SCALE_F64_e64 : AMDGPU::V_DIV_SCALE_F32_e64; 0
978 ----
979 // src0_modifiers, src0, src1_modifiers, src1, src2_modifiers, src2, clamp, ----
980 // omod ----
981 SDValue Ops[8]; 0
982 SelectVOP3BMods0(N->getOperand(0), Ops[1], Ops[0], Ops[6], Ops[7]); 0
983 SelectVOP3BMods(N->getOperand(1), Ops[3], Ops[2]); 0
984 SelectVOP3BMods(N->getOperand(2), Ops[5], Ops[4]); 0
985 CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, Opc, N->getVTList(), Ops); 0
986 } 0
987 ----
988 // We need to handle this here because tablegen doesn't support matching ----
989 // instructions with multiple outputs. ----
990 void AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectMAD_64_32(SDNode *N) { 0
991 SDLoc SL(N); 0
992 bool Signed = N->getOpcode() == AMDGPUISD::MAD_I64_I32; 0
993 unsigned Opc; ----
994 if (Subtarget->hasMADIntraFwdBug()) 0
995 Opc = Signed ? AMDGPU::V_MAD_I64_I32_gfx11_e64 0
996 : AMDGPU::V_MAD_U64_U32_gfx11_e64; ----
997 else ----
998 Opc = Signed ? AMDGPU::V_MAD_I64_I32_e64 : AMDGPU::V_MAD_U64_U32_e64; 0
999 ----
1000 SDValue Clamp = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, SL, MVT::i1); 0
1001 SDValue Ops[] = { N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1), N->getOperand(2), 0
1002 Clamp }; 0
1003 CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, Opc, N->getVTList(), Ops); 0
1004 } 0
1005 ----
1006 // We need to handle this here because tablegen doesn't support matching ----
1007 // instructions with multiple outputs. ----
1008 void AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectMUL_LOHI(SDNode *N) { 0
1009 SDLoc SL(N); 0
1010 bool Signed = N->getOpcode() == ISD::SMUL_LOHI; 0
1011 unsigned Opc; ----
1012 if (Subtarget->hasMADIntraFwdBug()) 0
1013 Opc = Signed ? AMDGPU::V_MAD_I64_I32_gfx11_e64 0
1014 : AMDGPU::V_MAD_U64_U32_gfx11_e64; ----
1015 else ----
1016 Opc = Signed ? AMDGPU::V_MAD_I64_I32_e64 : AMDGPU::V_MAD_U64_U32_e64; 0
1017 ----
1018 SDValue Zero = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, SL, MVT::i64); 0
1019 SDValue Clamp = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, SL, MVT::i1); 0
1020 SDValue Ops[] = {N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1), Zero, Clamp}; 0
1021 SDNode *Mad = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, SL, N->getVTList(), Ops); 0
1022 if (!SDValue(N, 0).use_empty()) { 0
1023 SDValue Sub0 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub0, SL, MVT::i32); 0
1024 SDNode *Lo = CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::EXTRACT_SUBREG, SL, 0
1025 MVT::i32, SDValue(Mad, 0), Sub0); ----
1026 ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, 0), SDValue(Lo, 0)); 0
1027 } ----
1028 if (!SDValue(N, 1).use_empty()) { 0
1029 SDValue Sub1 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub1, SL, MVT::i32); 0
1030 SDNode *Hi = CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::EXTRACT_SUBREG, SL, 0
1031 MVT::i32, SDValue(Mad, 0), Sub1); ----
1032 ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, 1), SDValue(Hi, 0)); 0
1033 } ----
1034 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(N); 0
1035 } 0
1036 ----
1037 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::isDSOffsetLegal(SDValue Base, unsigned Offset) const { 0
1038 if (!isUInt<16>(Offset)) 0
1039 return false; 0
1040 ----
1041 if (!Base || Subtarget->hasUsableDSOffset() || 0
1042 Subtarget->unsafeDSOffsetFoldingEnabled()) 0
1043 return true; 0
1044 ----
1045 // On Southern Islands instruction with a negative base value and an offset ----
1046 // don't seem to work. ----
1047 return CurDAG->SignBitIsZero(Base); 0
1048 } ----
1049 ----
1050 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectDS1Addr1Offset(SDValue Addr, SDValue &Base, 0
1051 SDValue &Offset) const { ----
1052 SDLoc DL(Addr); 0
1053 if (CurDAG->isBaseWithConstantOffset(Addr)) { 0
1054 SDValue N0 = Addr.getOperand(0); 0
1055 SDValue N1 = Addr.getOperand(1); 0
1056 ConstantSDNode *C1 = cast(N1); 0
1057 if (isDSOffsetLegal(N0, C1->getSExtValue())) { 0
1058 // (add n0, c0) ----
1059 Base = N0; 0
1060 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(C1->getZExtValue(), DL, MVT::i16); 0
1061 return true; 0
1062 } ----
1063 } else if (Addr.getOpcode() == ISD::SUB) { 0
1064 // sub C, x -> add (sub 0, x), C ----
1065 if (const ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(Addr.getOperand(0))) { 0
1066 int64_t ByteOffset = C->getSExtValue(); 0
1067 if (isDSOffsetLegal(SDValue(), ByteOffset)) { 0
1068 SDValue Zero = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1069 ----
1070 // XXX - This is kind of hacky. Create a dummy sub node so we can check ----
1071 // the known bits in isDSOffsetLegal. We need to emit the selected node ----
1072 // here, so this is thrown away. ----
1073 SDValue Sub = CurDAG->getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, MVT::i32, 0
1074 Zero, Addr.getOperand(1)); 0
1075 ----
1076 if (isDSOffsetLegal(Sub, ByteOffset)) { 0
1077 SmallVector Opnds; 0
1078 Opnds.push_back(Zero); 0
1079 Opnds.push_back(Addr.getOperand(1)); 0
1080 ----
1081 // FIXME: Select to VOP3 version for with-carry. ----
1082 unsigned SubOp = AMDGPU::V_SUB_CO_U32_e32; 0
1083 if (Subtarget->hasAddNoCarry()) { 0
1084 SubOp = AMDGPU::V_SUB_U32_e64; 0
1085 Opnds.push_back( 0
1086 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, {}, MVT::i1)); // clamp bit 0
1087 } ----
1088 ----
1089 MachineSDNode *MachineSub = ----
1090 CurDAG->getMachineNode(SubOp, DL, MVT::i32, Opnds); 0
1091 ----
1092 Base = SDValue(MachineSub, 0); 0
1093 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ByteOffset, DL, MVT::i16); 0
1094 return true; 0
1095 } 0
1096 } ----
1097 } ----
1098 } else if (const ConstantSDNode *CAddr = dyn_cast(Addr)) { 0
1099 // If we have a constant address, prefer to put the constant into the ----
1100 // offset. This can save moves to load the constant address since multiple ----
1101 // operations can share the zero base address register, and enables merging ----
1102 // into read2 / write2 instructions. ----
1103 ----
1104 SDLoc DL(Addr); 0
1105 ----
1106 if (isDSOffsetLegal(SDValue(), CAddr->getZExtValue())) { 0
1107 SDValue Zero = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1108 MachineSDNode *MovZero = CurDAG->getMachineNode(AMDGPU::V_MOV_B32_e32, 0
1109 DL, MVT::i32, Zero); ----
1110 Base = SDValue(MovZero, 0); 0
1111 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(CAddr->getZExtValue(), DL, MVT::i16); 0
1112 return true; 0
1113 } ----
1114 } 0
1115 ----
1116 // default case ----
1117 Base = Addr; 0
1118 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, SDLoc(Addr), MVT::i16); 0
1119 return true; 0
1120 } 0
1121 ----
1122 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::isDSOffset2Legal(SDValue Base, unsigned Offset0, 0
1123 unsigned Offset1, ----
1124 unsigned Size) const { ----
1125 if (Offset0 % Size != 0 || Offset1 % Size != 0) 0
1126 return false; 0
1127 if (!isUInt<8>(Offset0 / Size) || !isUInt<8>(Offset1 / Size)) 0
1128 return false; 0
1129 ----
1130 if (!Base || Subtarget->hasUsableDSOffset() || 0
1131 Subtarget->unsafeDSOffsetFoldingEnabled()) 0
1132 return true; 0
1133 ----
1134 // On Southern Islands instruction with a negative base value and an offset ----
1135 // don't seem to work. ----
1136 return CurDAG->SignBitIsZero(Base); 0
1137 } ----
1138 ----
1139 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::isFlatScratchBaseLegal(SDValue Base, 0
1140 uint64_t FlatVariant) const { ----
1141 if (FlatVariant != SIInstrFlags::FlatScratch) 0
1142 return true; 0
1143 // When value in 32-bit Base can be negative calculate scratch offset using ----
1144 // 32-bit add instruction, otherwise use Base(unsigned) + offset. ----
1145 return CurDAG->SignBitIsZero(Base); 0
1146 } ----
1147 ----
1148 // TODO: If offset is too big, put low 16-bit into offset. ----
1149 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectDS64Bit4ByteAligned(SDValue Addr, SDValue &Base, 0
1150 SDValue &Offset0, ----
1151 SDValue &Offset1) const { ----
1152 return SelectDSReadWrite2(Addr, Base, Offset0, Offset1, 4); 0
1153 } ----
1154 ----
1155 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectDS128Bit8ByteAligned(SDValue Addr, SDValue &Base, 0
1156 SDValue &Offset0, ----
1157 SDValue &Offset1) const { ----
1158 return SelectDSReadWrite2(Addr, Base, Offset0, Offset1, 8); 0
1159 } ----
1160 ----
1161 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectDSReadWrite2(SDValue Addr, SDValue &Base, 0
1162 SDValue &Offset0, SDValue &Offset1, ----
1163 unsigned Size) const { ----
1164 SDLoc DL(Addr); 0
1165 ----
1166 if (CurDAG->isBaseWithConstantOffset(Addr)) { 0
1167 SDValue N0 = Addr.getOperand(0); 0
1168 SDValue N1 = Addr.getOperand(1); 0
1169 ConstantSDNode *C1 = cast(N1); 0
1170 unsigned OffsetValue0 = C1->getZExtValue(); 0
1171 unsigned OffsetValue1 = OffsetValue0 + Size; 0
1172 ----
1173 // (add n0, c0) ----
1174 if (isDSOffset2Legal(N0, OffsetValue0, OffsetValue1, Size)) { 0
1175 Base = N0; 0
1176 Offset0 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(OffsetValue0 / Size, DL, MVT::i8); 0
1177 Offset1 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(OffsetValue1 / Size, DL, MVT::i8); 0
1178 return true; 0
1179 } ----
1180 } else if (Addr.getOpcode() == ISD::SUB) { 0
1181 // sub C, x -> add (sub 0, x), C ----
1182 if (const ConstantSDNode *C = 0
1183 dyn_cast(Addr.getOperand(0))) { 0
1184 unsigned OffsetValue0 = C->getZExtValue(); 0
1185 unsigned OffsetValue1 = OffsetValue0 + Size; 0
1186 ----
1187 if (isDSOffset2Legal(SDValue(), OffsetValue0, OffsetValue1, Size)) { 0
1188 SDLoc DL(Addr); 0
1189 SDValue Zero = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1190 ----
1191 // XXX - This is kind of hacky. Create a dummy sub node so we can check ----
1192 // the known bits in isDSOffsetLegal. We need to emit the selected node ----
1193 // here, so this is thrown away. ----
1194 SDValue Sub = ----
1195 CurDAG->getNode(ISD::SUB, DL, MVT::i32, Zero, Addr.getOperand(1)); 0
1196 ----
1197 if (isDSOffset2Legal(Sub, OffsetValue0, OffsetValue1, Size)) { 0
1198 SmallVector Opnds; 0
1199 Opnds.push_back(Zero); 0
1200 Opnds.push_back(Addr.getOperand(1)); 0
1201 unsigned SubOp = AMDGPU::V_SUB_CO_U32_e32; 0
1202 if (Subtarget->hasAddNoCarry()) { 0
1203 SubOp = AMDGPU::V_SUB_U32_e64; 0
1204 Opnds.push_back( 0
1205 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, {}, MVT::i1)); // clamp bit 0
1206 } ----
1207 ----
1208 MachineSDNode *MachineSub = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1209 SubOp, DL, MVT::getIntegerVT(Size * 8), Opnds); ----
1210 ----
1211 Base = SDValue(MachineSub, 0); 0
1212 Offset0 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(OffsetValue0 / Size, DL, MVT::i8); 0
1213 Offset1 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(OffsetValue1 / Size, DL, MVT::i8); 0
1214 return true; 0
1215 } 0
1216 } 0
1217 } ----
1218 } else if (const ConstantSDNode *CAddr = dyn_cast(Addr)) { 0
1219 unsigned OffsetValue0 = CAddr->getZExtValue(); 0
1220 unsigned OffsetValue1 = OffsetValue0 + Size; 0
1221 ----
1222 if (isDSOffset2Legal(SDValue(), OffsetValue0, OffsetValue1, Size)) { 0
1223 SDValue Zero = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1224 MachineSDNode *MovZero = ----
1225 CurDAG->getMachineNode(AMDGPU::V_MOV_B32_e32, DL, MVT::i32, Zero); 0
1226 Base = SDValue(MovZero, 0); 0
1227 Offset0 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(OffsetValue0 / Size, DL, MVT::i8); 0
1228 Offset1 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(OffsetValue1 / Size, DL, MVT::i8); 0
1229 return true; 0
1230 } ----
1231 } ----
1232 ----
1233 // default case ----
1234 ----
1235 Base = Addr; 0
1236 Offset0 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i8); 0
1237 Offset1 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(1, DL, MVT::i8); 0
1238 return true; 0
1239 } 0
1240 ----
1241 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectMUBUF(SDValue Addr, SDValue &Ptr, SDValue &VAddr, 0
1242 SDValue &SOffset, SDValue &Offset, ----
1243 SDValue &Offen, SDValue &Idxen, ----
1244 SDValue &Addr64) const { ----
1245 // Subtarget prefers to use flat instruction ----
1246 // FIXME: This should be a pattern predicate and not reach here ----
1247 if (Subtarget->useFlatForGlobal()) 0
1248 return false; 0
1249 ----
1250 SDLoc DL(Addr); 0
1251 ----
1252 Idxen = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i1); 0
1253 Offen = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i1); 0
1254 Addr64 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i1); 0
1255 SOffset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1256 ----
1257 ConstantSDNode *C1 = nullptr; 0
1258 SDValue N0 = Addr; 0
1259 if (CurDAG->isBaseWithConstantOffset(Addr)) { 0
1260 C1 = cast(Addr.getOperand(1)); 0
1261 if (isUInt<32>(C1->getZExtValue())) 0
1262 N0 = Addr.getOperand(0); 0
1263 else ----
1264 C1 = nullptr; 0
1265 } ----
1266 ----
1267 if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD) { 0
1268 // (add N2, N3) -> addr64, or ----
1269 // (add (add N2, N3), C1) -> addr64 ----
1270 SDValue N2 = N0.getOperand(0); 0
1271 SDValue N3 = N0.getOperand(1); 0
1272 Addr64 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(1, DL, MVT::i1); 0
1273 ----
1274 if (N2->isDivergent()) { 0
1275 if (N3->isDivergent()) { 0
1276 // Both N2 and N3 are divergent. Use N0 (the result of the add) as the ----
1277 // addr64, and construct the resource from a 0 address. ----
1278 Ptr = SDValue(buildSMovImm64(DL, 0, MVT::v2i32), 0); 0
1279 VAddr = N0; 0
1280 } else { ----
1281 // N2 is divergent, N3 is not. ----
1282 Ptr = N3; 0
1283 VAddr = N2; 0
1284 } ----
1285 } else { ----
1286 // N2 is not divergent. ----
1287 Ptr = N2; 0
1288 VAddr = N3; 0
1289 } ----
1290 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1291 } else if (N0->isDivergent()) { 0
1292 // N0 is divergent. Use it as the addr64, and construct the resource from a ----
1293 // 0 address. ----
1294 Ptr = SDValue(buildSMovImm64(DL, 0, MVT::v2i32), 0); 0
1295 VAddr = N0; 0
1296 Addr64 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(1, DL, MVT::i1); 0
1297 } else { ----
1298 // N0 -> offset, or ----
1299 // (N0 + C1) -> offset ----
1300 VAddr = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1301 Ptr = N0; 0
1302 } ----
1303 ----
1304 if (!C1) { 0
1305 // No offset. ----
1306 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1307 return true; 0
1308 } ----
1309 ----
1310 if (SIInstrInfo::isLegalMUBUFImmOffset(C1->getZExtValue())) { 0
1311 // Legal offset for instruction. ----
1312 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(C1->getZExtValue(), DL, MVT::i32); 0
1313 return true; 0
1314 } ----
1315 ----
1316 // Illegal offset, store it in soffset. ----
1317 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1318 SOffset = 0
1319 SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1320 AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32, DL, MVT::i32, ----
1321 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(C1->getZExtValue(), DL, MVT::i32)), 0
1322 0); ----
1323 return true; 0
1324 } 0
1325 ----
1326 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectMUBUFAddr64(SDValue Addr, SDValue &SRsrc, 0
1327 SDValue &VAddr, SDValue &SOffset, ----
1328 SDValue &Offset) const { ----
1329 SDValue Ptr, Offen, Idxen, Addr64; 0
1330 ----
1331 // addr64 bit was removed for volcanic islands. ----
1332 // FIXME: This should be a pattern predicate and not reach here ----
1333 if (!Subtarget->hasAddr64()) 0
1334 return false; 0
1335 ----
1336 if (!SelectMUBUF(Addr, Ptr, VAddr, SOffset, Offset, Offen, Idxen, Addr64)) 0
1337 return false; 0
1338 ----
1339 ConstantSDNode *C = cast(Addr64); 0
1340 if (C->getSExtValue()) { 0
1341 SDLoc DL(Addr); 0
1342 ----
1343 const SITargetLowering& Lowering = ----
1344 *static_cast(getTargetLowering()); 0
1345 ----
1346 SRsrc = SDValue(Lowering.wrapAddr64Rsrc(*CurDAG, DL, Ptr), 0); 0
1347 return true; 0
1348 } 0
1349 ----
1350 return false; 0
1351 } ----
1352 ----
1353 std::pair AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::foldFrameIndex(SDValue N) const { 0
1354 SDLoc DL(N); 0
1355 ----
1356 auto *FI = dyn_cast(N); 0
1357 SDValue TFI = ----
1358 FI ? CurDAG->getTargetFrameIndex(FI->getIndex(), FI->getValueType(0)) : N; 0
1359 ----
1360 // We rebase the base address into an absolute stack address and hence ----
1361 // use constant 0 for soffset. This value must be retained until ----
1362 // frame elimination and eliminateFrameIndex will choose the appropriate ----
1363 // frame register if need be. ----
1364 return std::pair(TFI, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
1365 } 0
1366 ----
1367 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectMUBUFScratchOffen(SDNode *Parent, 0
1368 SDValue Addr, SDValue &Rsrc, ----
1369 SDValue &VAddr, SDValue &SOffset, ----
1370 SDValue &ImmOffset) const { ----
1371 ----
1372 SDLoc DL(Addr); 0
1373 MachineFunction &MF = CurDAG->getMachineFunction(); 0
1374 const SIMachineFunctionInfo *Info = MF.getInfo(); 0
1375 ----
1376 Rsrc = CurDAG->getRegister(Info->getScratchRSrcReg(), MVT::v4i32); 0
1377 ----
1378 if (ConstantSDNode *CAddr = dyn_cast(Addr)) { 0
1379 int64_t Imm = CAddr->getSExtValue(); 0
1380 const int64_t NullPtr = ----
1381 AMDGPUTargetMachine::getNullPointerValue(AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS); 0
1382 // Don't fold null pointer. ----
1383 if (Imm != NullPtr) { 0
1384 const uint32_t MaxOffset = SIInstrInfo::getMaxMUBUFImmOffset(); 0
1385 SDValue HighBits = ----
1386 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Imm & ~MaxOffset, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1387 MachineSDNode *MovHighBits = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1388 AMDGPU::V_MOV_B32_e32, DL, MVT::i32, HighBits); ----
1389 VAddr = SDValue(MovHighBits, 0); 0
1390 ----
1391 SOffset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1392 ImmOffset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Imm & MaxOffset, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1393 return true; 0
1394 } ----
1395 } ----
1396 ----
1397 if (CurDAG->isBaseWithConstantOffset(Addr)) { 0
1398 // (add n0, c1) ----
1399 ----
1400 SDValue N0 = Addr.getOperand(0); 0
1401 SDValue N1 = Addr.getOperand(1); 0
1402 ----
1403 // Offsets in vaddr must be positive if range checking is enabled. ----
1404 // ----
1405 // The total computation of vaddr + soffset + offset must not overflow. If ----
1406 // vaddr is negative, even if offset is 0 the sgpr offset add will end up ----
1407 // overflowing. ----
1408 // ----
1409 // Prior to gfx9, MUBUF instructions with the vaddr offset enabled would ----
1410 // always perform a range check. If a negative vaddr base index was used, ----
1411 // this would fail the range check. The overall address computation would ----
1412 // compute a valid address, but this doesn't happen due to the range ----
1413 // check. For out-of-bounds MUBUF loads, a 0 is returned. ----
1414 // ----
1415 // Therefore it should be safe to fold any VGPR offset on gfx9 into the ----
1416 // MUBUF vaddr, but not on older subtargets which can only do this if the ----
1417 // sign bit is known 0. ----
1418 ConstantSDNode *C1 = cast(N1); 0
1419 if (SIInstrInfo::isLegalMUBUFImmOffset(C1->getZExtValue()) && 0
1420 (!Subtarget->privateMemoryResourceIsRangeChecked() || 0
1421 CurDAG->SignBitIsZero(N0))) { 0
1422 std::tie(VAddr, SOffset) = foldFrameIndex(N0); 0
1423 ImmOffset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(C1->getZExtValue(), DL, MVT::i32); 0
1424 return true; 0
1425 } ----
1426 } ----
1427 ----
1428 // (node) ----
1429 std::tie(VAddr, SOffset) = foldFrameIndex(Addr); 0
1430 ImmOffset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1431 return true; 0
1432 } 0
1433 ----
1434 static bool IsCopyFromSGPR(const SIRegisterInfo &TRI, SDValue Val) { 0
1435 if (Val.getOpcode() != ISD::CopyFromReg) 0
1436 return false; 0
1437 auto Reg = cast(Val.getOperand(1))->getReg(); 0
1438 if (!Reg.isPhysical()) 0
1439 return false; 0
1440 auto RC = TRI.getPhysRegBaseClass(Reg); 0
1441 return RC && TRI.isSGPRClass(RC); 0
1442 } ----
1443 ----
1444 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectMUBUFScratchOffset(SDNode *Parent, 0
1445 SDValue Addr, ----
1446 SDValue &SRsrc, ----
1447 SDValue &SOffset, ----
1448 SDValue &Offset) const { ----
1449 const SIRegisterInfo *TRI = ----
1450 static_cast(Subtarget->getRegisterInfo()); 0
1451 MachineFunction &MF = CurDAG->getMachineFunction(); 0
1452 const SIMachineFunctionInfo *Info = MF.getInfo(); 0
1453 SDLoc DL(Addr); 0
1454 ----
1455 // CopyFromReg ----
1456 if (IsCopyFromSGPR(*TRI, Addr)) { 0
1457 SRsrc = CurDAG->getRegister(Info->getScratchRSrcReg(), MVT::v4i32); 0
1458 SOffset = Addr; 0
1459 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1460 return true; 0
1461 } ----
1462 ----
1463 ConstantSDNode *CAddr; ----
1464 if (Addr.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD) { 0
1465 // Add (CopyFromReg ) ----
1466 CAddr = dyn_cast(Addr.getOperand(1)); 0
1467 if (!CAddr || !SIInstrInfo::isLegalMUBUFImmOffset(CAddr->getZExtValue())) 0
1468 return false; 0
1469 if (!IsCopyFromSGPR(*TRI, Addr.getOperand(0))) 0
1470 return false; 0
1471 ----
1472 SOffset = Addr.getOperand(0); 0
1473 } else if ((CAddr = dyn_cast(Addr)) && 0
1474 SIInstrInfo::isLegalMUBUFImmOffset(CAddr->getZExtValue())) { 0
1475 // ----
1476 SOffset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1477 } else { ----
1478 return false; 0
1479 } ----
1480 ----
1481 SRsrc = CurDAG->getRegister(Info->getScratchRSrcReg(), MVT::v4i32); 0
1482 ----
1483 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(CAddr->getZExtValue(), DL, MVT::i32); 0
1484 return true; 0
1485 } 0
1486 ----
1487 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectMUBUFOffset(SDValue Addr, SDValue &SRsrc, 0
1488 SDValue &SOffset, SDValue &Offset ----
1489 ) const { ----
1490 SDValue Ptr, VAddr, Offen, Idxen, Addr64; 0
1491 const SIInstrInfo *TII = ----
1492 static_cast(Subtarget->getInstrInfo()); 0
1493 ----
1494 if (!SelectMUBUF(Addr, Ptr, VAddr, SOffset, Offset, Offen, Idxen, Addr64)) 0
1495 return false; 0
1496 ----
1497 if (!cast(Offen)->getSExtValue() && 0
1498 !cast(Idxen)->getSExtValue() && 0
1499 !cast(Addr64)->getSExtValue()) { 0
1500 uint64_t Rsrc = TII->getDefaultRsrcDataFormat() | 0
1501 APInt::getAllOnes(32).getZExtValue(); // Size 0
1502 SDLoc DL(Addr); 0
1503 ----
1504 const SITargetLowering& Lowering = ----
1505 *static_cast(getTargetLowering()); 0
1506 ----
1507 SRsrc = SDValue(Lowering.buildRSRC(*CurDAG, DL, Ptr, 0, Rsrc), 0); 0
1508 return true; 0
1509 } 0
1510 return false; 0
1511 } ----
1512 ----
1513 // Find a load or store from corresponding pattern root. ----
1514 // Roots may be build_vector, bitconvert or their combinations. ----
1515 static MemSDNode* findMemSDNode(SDNode *N) { 0
1516 N = AMDGPUTargetLowering::stripBitcast(SDValue(N,0)).getNode(); 0
1517 if (MemSDNode *MN = dyn_cast(N)) 0
1518 return MN; 0
1519 assert(isa(N)); 0
1520 for (SDValue V : N->op_values()) 0
1521 if (MemSDNode *MN = 0
1522 dyn_cast(AMDGPUTargetLowering::stripBitcast(V))) 0
1523 return MN; 0
1524 llvm_unreachable("cannot find MemSDNode in the pattern!"); 0
1525 } ----
1526 ----
1527 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectFlatOffsetImpl(SDNode *N, SDValue Addr, 0
1528 SDValue &VAddr, SDValue &Offset, ----
1529 uint64_t FlatVariant) const { ----
1530 int64_t OffsetVal = 0; 0
1531 ----
1532 unsigned AS = findMemSDNode(N)->getAddressSpace(); 0
1533 ----
1534 bool CanHaveFlatSegmentOffsetBug = ----
1535 Subtarget->hasFlatSegmentOffsetBug() && 0
1536 FlatVariant == SIInstrFlags::FLAT && 0
1537 (AS == AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS || AS == AMDGPUAS::GLOBAL_ADDRESS); 0
1538 ----
1539 if (Subtarget->hasFlatInstOffsets() && !CanHaveFlatSegmentOffsetBug) { 0
1540 SDValue N0, N1; 0
1541 if (isBaseWithConstantOffset64(Addr, N0, N1) && 0
1542 isFlatScratchBaseLegal(N0, FlatVariant)) { 0
1543 int64_t COffsetVal = cast(N1)->getSExtValue(); 0
1544 ----
1545 const SIInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget->getInstrInfo(); 0
1546 if (TII->isLegalFLATOffset(COffsetVal, AS, FlatVariant)) { 0
1547 Addr = N0; 0
1548 OffsetVal = COffsetVal; 0
1549 } else { ----
1550 // If the offset doesn't fit, put the low bits into the offset field and ----
1551 // add the rest. ----
1552 // ----
1553 // For a FLAT instruction the hardware decides whether to access ----
1554 // global/scratch/shared memory based on the high bits of vaddr, ----
1555 // ignoring the offset field, so we have to ensure that when we add ----
1556 // remainder to vaddr it still points into the same underlying object. ----
1557 // The easiest way to do that is to make sure that we split the offset ----
1558 // into two pieces that are both >= 0 or both <= 0. ----
1559 ----
1560 SDLoc DL(N); 0
1561 uint64_t RemainderOffset; ----
1562 ----
1563 std::tie(OffsetVal, RemainderOffset) = 0
1564 TII->splitFlatOffset(COffsetVal, AS, FlatVariant); 0
1565 ----
1566 SDValue AddOffsetLo = ----
1567 getMaterializedScalarImm32(Lo_32(RemainderOffset), DL); 0
1568 SDValue Clamp = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i1); 0
1569 ----
1570 if (Addr.getValueType().getSizeInBits() == 32) { 0
1571 SmallVector Opnds; 0
1572 Opnds.push_back(N0); 0
1573 Opnds.push_back(AddOffsetLo); 0
1574 unsigned AddOp = AMDGPU::V_ADD_CO_U32_e32; 0
1575 if (Subtarget->hasAddNoCarry()) { 0
1576 AddOp = AMDGPU::V_ADD_U32_e64; 0
1577 Opnds.push_back(Clamp); 0
1578 } ----
1579 Addr = SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode(AddOp, DL, MVT::i32, Opnds), 0); 0
1580 } else { 0
1581 // TODO: Should this try to use a scalar add pseudo if the base address ----
1582 // is uniform and saddr is usable? ----
1583 SDValue Sub0 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1584 SDValue Sub1 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub1, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1585 ----
1586 SDNode *N0Lo = CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::EXTRACT_SUBREG, 0
1587 DL, MVT::i32, N0, Sub0); ----
1588 SDNode *N0Hi = CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::EXTRACT_SUBREG, 0
1589 DL, MVT::i32, N0, Sub1); ----
1590 ----
1591 SDValue AddOffsetHi = ----
1592 getMaterializedScalarImm32(Hi_32(RemainderOffset), DL); 0
1593 ----
1594 SDVTList VTs = CurDAG->getVTList(MVT::i32, MVT::i1); 0
1595 ----
1596 SDNode *Add = ----
1597 CurDAG->getMachineNode(AMDGPU::V_ADD_CO_U32_e64, DL, VTs, 0
1598 {AddOffsetLo, SDValue(N0Lo, 0), Clamp}); ----
1599 ----
1600 SDNode *Addc = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1601 AMDGPU::V_ADDC_U32_e64, DL, VTs, ----
1602 {AddOffsetHi, SDValue(N0Hi, 0), SDValue(Add, 1), Clamp}); ----
1603 ----
1604 SDValue RegSequenceArgs[] = { ----
1605 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::VReg_64RegClassID, DL, MVT::i32), 0
1606 SDValue(Add, 0), Sub0, SDValue(Addc, 0), Sub1}; 0
1607 ----
1608 Addr = SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode(AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE, DL, 0
1609 MVT::i64, RegSequenceArgs), ----
1610 0); ----
1611 } ----
1612 } 0
1613 } ----
1614 } ----
1615 ----
1616 VAddr = Addr; 0
1617 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(OffsetVal, SDLoc(), MVT::i16); 0
1618 return true; 0
1619 } ----

1622 SDValue &VAddr, ----
1623 SDValue &Offset) const { ----

1633 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectScratchOffset(SDNode *N, SDValue Addr, 0
1634 SDValue &VAddr, ----
1635 SDValue &Offset) const { ----
1636 return SelectFlatOffsetImpl(N, Addr, VAddr, Offset, 0
1637 SIInstrFlags::FlatScratch); 0
1638 } ----
1639 ----
1640 // If this matches zero_extend i32:x, return x ----
1641 static SDValue matchZExtFromI32(SDValue Op) { 0
1642 if (Op.getOpcode() != ISD::ZERO_EXTEND) 0
1643 return SDValue(); 0
1644 ----
1645 SDValue ExtSrc = Op.getOperand(0); 0
1646 return (ExtSrc.getValueType() == MVT::i32) ? ExtSrc : SDValue(); 0
1647 } ----
1648 ----
1649 // Match (64-bit SGPR base) + (zext vgpr offset) + sext(imm offset) ----
1650 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectGlobalSAddr(SDNode *N, 0
1651 SDValue Addr, ----
1652 SDValue &SAddr, ----
1653 SDValue &VOffset, ----
1654 SDValue &Offset) const { ----
1655 int64_t ImmOffset = 0; 0
1656 ----
1657 // Match the immediate offset first, which canonically is moved as low as ----
1658 // possible. ----
1659 ----
1660 SDValue LHS, RHS; 0
1661 if (isBaseWithConstantOffset64(Addr, LHS, RHS)) { 0
1662 int64_t COffsetVal = cast(RHS)->getSExtValue(); 0
1663 const SIInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget->getInstrInfo(); 0
1664 ----
1665 if (TII->isLegalFLATOffset(COffsetVal, AMDGPUAS::GLOBAL_ADDRESS, 0
1666 SIInstrFlags::FlatGlobal)) { ----
1667 Addr = LHS; 0
1668 ImmOffset = COffsetVal; 0
1669 } else if (!LHS->isDivergent()) { 0
1670 if (COffsetVal > 0) { 0
1671 SDLoc SL(N); 0
1672 // saddr + large_offset -> saddr + ----
1673 // (voffset = large_offset & ~MaxOffset) + ----
1674 // (large_offset & MaxOffset); ----
1675 int64_t SplitImmOffset, RemainderOffset; ----
1676 std::tie(SplitImmOffset, RemainderOffset) = TII->splitFlatOffset( 0
1677 COffsetVal, AMDGPUAS::GLOBAL_ADDRESS, SIInstrFlags::FlatGlobal); 0
1678 ----
1679 if (isUInt<32>(RemainderOffset)) { 0
1680 SDNode *VMov = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1681 AMDGPU::V_MOV_B32_e32, SL, MVT::i32, ----
1682 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RemainderOffset, SDLoc(), MVT::i32)); 0
1683 VOffset = SDValue(VMov, 0); 0
1684 SAddr = LHS; 0
1685 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(SplitImmOffset, SDLoc(), MVT::i16); 0
1686 return true; 0
1687 } ----
1688 } 0
1689 ----
1690 // We are adding a 64 bit SGPR and a constant. If constant bus limit ----
1691 // is 1 we would need to perform 1 or 2 extra moves for each half of ----
1692 // the constant and it is better to do a scalar add and then issue a ----
1693 // single VALU instruction to materialize zero. Otherwise it is less ----
1694 // instructions to perform VALU adds with immediates or inline literals. ----
1695 unsigned NumLiterals = ----
1696 !TII->isInlineConstant(APInt(32, COffsetVal & 0xffffffff)) + 0
1697 !TII->isInlineConstant(APInt(32, COffsetVal >> 32)); 0
1698 if (Subtarget->getConstantBusLimit(AMDGPU::V_ADD_U32_e64) > NumLiterals) 0
1699 return false; 0
1700 } ----
1701 } ----
1702 ----
1703 // Match the variable offset. ----
1704 if (Addr.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD) { 0
1705 LHS = Addr.getOperand(0); 0
1706 RHS = Addr.getOperand(1); 0
1707 ----
1708 if (!LHS->isDivergent()) { 0
1709 // add (i64 sgpr), (zero_extend (i32 vgpr)) ----
1710 if (SDValue ZextRHS = matchZExtFromI32(RHS)) { 0
1711 SAddr = LHS; 0
1712 VOffset = ZextRHS; 0
1713 } ----
1714 } ----
1715 ----
1716 if (!SAddr && !RHS->isDivergent()) { 0
1717 // add (zero_extend (i32 vgpr)), (i64 sgpr) ----
1718 if (SDValue ZextLHS = matchZExtFromI32(LHS)) { 0
1719 SAddr = RHS; 0
1720 VOffset = ZextLHS; 0
1721 } ----
1722 } ----
1723 ----
1724 if (SAddr) { 0
1725 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmOffset, SDLoc(), MVT::i16); 0
1726 return true; 0
1727 } ----
1728 } ----
1729 ----
1730 if (Addr->isDivergent() || Addr.getOpcode() == ISD::UNDEF || 0
1731 isa(Addr)) 0
1732 return false; 0
1733 ----
1734 // It's cheaper to materialize a single 32-bit zero for vaddr than the two ----
1735 // moves required to copy a 64-bit SGPR to VGPR. ----
1736 SAddr = Addr; 0
1737 SDNode *VMov = ----
1738 CurDAG->getMachineNode(AMDGPU::V_MOV_B32_e32, SDLoc(Addr), MVT::i32, 0
1739 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, SDLoc(), MVT::i32)); 0
1740 VOffset = SDValue(VMov, 0); 0
1741 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmOffset, SDLoc(), MVT::i16); 0
1742 return true; 0
1743 } ----
1744 ----
1745 static SDValue SelectSAddrFI(SelectionDAG *CurDAG, SDValue SAddr) { 0
1746 if (auto FI = dyn_cast(SAddr)) { 0
1747 SAddr = CurDAG->getTargetFrameIndex(FI->getIndex(), FI->getValueType(0)); 0
1748 } else if (SAddr.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD && 0
1749 isa(SAddr.getOperand(0))) { 0
1750 // Materialize this into a scalar move for scalar address to avoid ----
1751 // readfirstlane. ----
1752 auto FI = cast(SAddr.getOperand(0)); 0
1753 SDValue TFI = CurDAG->getTargetFrameIndex(FI->getIndex(), 0
1754 FI->getValueType(0)); ----
1755 SAddr = SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode(AMDGPU::S_ADD_I32, SDLoc(SAddr), 0
1756 MVT::i32, TFI, SAddr.getOperand(1)), 0
1757 0); ----
1758 } ----
1759 ----
1760 return SAddr; 0
1761 } ----
1762 ----
1763 // Match (32-bit SGPR base) + sext(imm offset) ----
1764 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectScratchSAddr(SDNode *Parent, SDValue Addr, 0
1765 SDValue &SAddr, ----
1766 SDValue &Offset) const { ----
1767 if (Addr->isDivergent()) 0
1768 return false; 0
1769 ----
1770 SDLoc DL(Addr); 0
1771 ----
1772 int64_t COffsetVal = 0; 0
1773 ----
1774 if (CurDAG->isBaseWithConstantOffset(Addr) && 0
1775 isFlatScratchBaseLegal(Addr.getOperand(0))) { 0
1776 COffsetVal = cast(Addr.getOperand(1))->getSExtValue(); 0
1777 SAddr = Addr.getOperand(0); 0
1778 } else { ----
1779 SAddr = Addr; 0
1780 } ----
1781 ----
1782 SAddr = SelectSAddrFI(CurDAG, SAddr); 0
1783 ----
1784 const SIInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget->getInstrInfo(); 0
1785 ----
1786 if (!TII->isLegalFLATOffset(COffsetVal, AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS, 0
1787 SIInstrFlags::FlatScratch)) { ----
1788 int64_t SplitImmOffset, RemainderOffset; ----
1789 std::tie(SplitImmOffset, RemainderOffset) = TII->splitFlatOffset( 0
1790 COffsetVal, AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS, SIInstrFlags::FlatScratch); 0
1791 ----
1792 COffsetVal = SplitImmOffset; 0
1793 ----
1794 SDValue AddOffset = ----
1795 SAddr.getOpcode() == ISD::TargetFrameIndex 0
1796 ? getMaterializedScalarImm32(Lo_32(RemainderOffset), DL) 0
1797 : CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RemainderOffset, DL, MVT::i32); 0
1798 SAddr = SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode(AMDGPU::S_ADD_I32, DL, MVT::i32, 0
1799 SAddr, AddOffset), ----
1800 0); ----
1801 } ----
1802 ----
1803 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(COffsetVal, DL, MVT::i16); 0
1804 ----
1805 return true; 0
1806 } 0
1807 ----
1808 // Check whether the flat scratch SVS swizzle bug affects this access. ----
1809 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::checkFlatScratchSVSSwizzleBug( 0
1810 SDValue VAddr, SDValue SAddr, uint64_t ImmOffset) const { ----
1811 if (!Subtarget->hasFlatScratchSVSSwizzleBug()) 0
1812 return false; 0
1813 ----
1814 // The bug affects the swizzling of SVS accesses if there is any carry out ----
1815 // from the two low order bits (i.e. from bit 1 into bit 2) when adding ----
1816 // voffset to (soffset + inst_offset). ----
1817 KnownBits VKnown = CurDAG->computeKnownBits(VAddr); 0
1818 KnownBits SKnown = KnownBits::computeForAddSub( ----
1819 true, false, CurDAG->computeKnownBits(SAddr), 0
1820 KnownBits::makeConstant(APInt(32, ImmOffset))); 0
1821 uint64_t VMax = VKnown.getMaxValue().getZExtValue(); 0
1822 uint64_t SMax = SKnown.getMaxValue().getZExtValue(); 0
1823 return (VMax & 3) + (SMax & 3) >= 4; 0
1824 } 0
1825 ----
1826 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectScratchSVAddr(SDNode *N, SDValue Addr, 0
1827 SDValue &VAddr, SDValue &SAddr, ----
1828 SDValue &Offset) const { ----
1829 int64_t ImmOffset = 0; 0
1830 ----
1831 SDValue LHS, RHS; 0
1832 if (isBaseWithConstantOffset64(Addr, LHS, RHS)) { 0
1833 int64_t COffsetVal = cast(RHS)->getSExtValue(); 0
1834 const SIInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget->getInstrInfo(); 0
1835 ----
1836 if (TII->isLegalFLATOffset(COffsetVal, AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS, true)) { 0
1837 Addr = LHS; 0
1838 ImmOffset = COffsetVal; 0
1839 } else if (!LHS->isDivergent() && COffsetVal > 0) { 0
1840 SDLoc SL(N); 0
1841 // saddr + large_offset -> saddr + (vaddr = large_offset & ~MaxOffset) + ----
1842 // (large_offset & MaxOffset); ----
1843 int64_t SplitImmOffset, RemainderOffset; ----
1844 std::tie(SplitImmOffset, RemainderOffset) 0
1845 = TII->splitFlatOffset(COffsetVal, AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS, true); 0
1846 ----
1847 if (isUInt<32>(RemainderOffset)) { 0
1848 SDNode *VMov = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1849 AMDGPU::V_MOV_B32_e32, SL, MVT::i32, ----
1850 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RemainderOffset, SDLoc(), MVT::i32)); 0
1851 VAddr = SDValue(VMov, 0); 0
1852 SAddr = LHS; 0
1853 if (!isFlatScratchBaseLegal(SAddr) || !isFlatScratchBaseLegal(VAddr)) 0
1854 return false; 0
1855 if (checkFlatScratchSVSSwizzleBug(VAddr, SAddr, SplitImmOffset)) 0
1856 return false; 0
1857 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(SplitImmOffset, SDLoc(), MVT::i16); 0
1858 return true; 0
1859 } ----
1860 } 0
1861 } ----
1862 ----
1863 if (Addr.getOpcode() != ISD::ADD) 0
1864 return false; 0
1865 ----
1866 LHS = Addr.getOperand(0); 0
1867 RHS = Addr.getOperand(1); 0
1868 ----
1869 if (!LHS->isDivergent() && RHS->isDivergent()) { 0
1870 SAddr = LHS; 0
1871 VAddr = RHS; 0
1872 } else if (!RHS->isDivergent() && LHS->isDivergent()) { 0
1873 SAddr = RHS; 0
1874 VAddr = LHS; 0
1875 } else { ----
1876 return false; 0
1877 } ----
1878 ----
1879 if (!isFlatScratchBaseLegal(SAddr) || !isFlatScratchBaseLegal(VAddr)) 0
1880 return false; 0
1881 ----
1882 if (checkFlatScratchSVSSwizzleBug(VAddr, SAddr, ImmOffset)) 0
1883 return false; 0
1884 SAddr = SelectSAddrFI(CurDAG, SAddr); 0
1885 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmOffset, SDLoc(), MVT::i16); 0
1886 return true; 0
1887 } ----
1888 ----
1889 // Match an immediate (if Offset is not null) or an SGPR (if SOffset is ----
1890 // not null) offset. If Imm32Only is true, match only 32-bit immediate ----
1891 // offsets available on CI. ----
1892 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectSMRDOffset(SDValue ByteOffsetNode, 0
1893 SDValue *SOffset, SDValue *Offset, ----
1894 bool Imm32Only, bool IsBuffer) const { ----
1895 assert((!SOffset || !Offset) && 0
1896 "Cannot match both soffset and offset at the same time!"); ----
1897 ----
1898 ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(ByteOffsetNode); 0
1899 if (!C) { 0
1900 if (!SOffset) 0
1901 return false; 0
1902 if (ByteOffsetNode.getValueType().isScalarInteger() && 0
1903 ByteOffsetNode.getValueType().getSizeInBits() == 32) { 0
1904 *SOffset = ByteOffsetNode; 0
1905 return true; 0
1906 } ----
1907 if (ByteOffsetNode.getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND) { 0
1908 if (ByteOffsetNode.getOperand(0).getValueType().getSizeInBits() == 32) { 0
1909 *SOffset = ByteOffsetNode.getOperand(0); 0
1910 return true; 0
1911 } ----
1912 } ----
1913 return false; 0
1914 } ----
1915 ----
1916 SDLoc SL(ByteOffsetNode); 0
1917 ----
1918 // GFX9 and GFX10 have signed byte immediate offsets. The immediate ----
1919 // offset for S_BUFFER instructions is unsigned. ----
1920 int64_t ByteOffset = IsBuffer ? C->getZExtValue() : C->getSExtValue(); 0
1921 std::optional EncodedOffset = ----
1922 AMDGPU::getSMRDEncodedOffset(*Subtarget, ByteOffset, IsBuffer); 0
1923 if (EncodedOffset && Offset && !Imm32Only) { 0
1924 *Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(*EncodedOffset, SL, MVT::i32); 0
1925 return true; 0
1926 } ----
1927 ----
1928 // SGPR and literal offsets are unsigned. ----
1929 if (ByteOffset < 0) 0
1930 return false; 0
1931 ----
1932 EncodedOffset = AMDGPU::getSMRDEncodedLiteralOffset32(*Subtarget, ByteOffset); 0
1933 if (EncodedOffset && Offset && Imm32Only) { 0
1934 *Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(*EncodedOffset, SL, MVT::i32); 0
1935 return true; 0
1936 } ----
1937 ----
1938 if (!isUInt<32>(ByteOffset) && !isInt<32>(ByteOffset)) 0
1939 return false; 0
1940 ----
1941 if (SOffset) { 0
1942 SDValue C32Bit = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ByteOffset, SL, MVT::i32); 0
1943 *SOffset = SDValue( 0
1944 CurDAG->getMachineNode(AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32, SL, MVT::i32, C32Bit), 0); 0
1945 return true; 0
1946 } ----
1947 ----
1948 return false; 0
1949 } 0
1950 ----
1951 SDValue AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::Expand32BitAddress(SDValue Addr) const { 0
1952 if (Addr.getValueType() != MVT::i32) 0
1953 return Addr; 0
1954 ----
1955 // Zero-extend a 32-bit address. ----
1956 SDLoc SL(Addr); 0
1957 ----
1958 const MachineFunction &MF = CurDAG->getMachineFunction(); 0
1959 const SIMachineFunctionInfo *Info = MF.getInfo(); 0
1960 unsigned AddrHiVal = Info->get32BitAddressHighBits(); 0
1961 SDValue AddrHi = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AddrHiVal, SL, MVT::i32); 0
1962 ----
1963 const SDValue Ops[] = { ----
1964 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::SReg_64_XEXECRegClassID, SL, MVT::i32), 0
1965 Addr, ----
1966 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub0, SL, MVT::i32), 0
1967 SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode(AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32, SL, MVT::i32, AddrHi), 0
1968 0), ----
1969 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub1, SL, MVT::i32), 0
1970 }; 0
1971 ----
1972 return SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode(AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE, SL, MVT::i64, 0
1973 Ops), 0); 0
1974 } 0
1975 ----
1976 // Match a base and an immediate (if Offset is not null) or an SGPR (if ----
1977 // SOffset is not null) or an immediate+SGPR offset. If Imm32Only is ----
1978 // true, match only 32-bit immediate offsets available on CI. ----
1979 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectSMRDBaseOffset(SDValue Addr, SDValue &SBase, 0
1980 SDValue *SOffset, SDValue *Offset, ----
1981 bool Imm32Only, ----
1982 bool IsBuffer) const { ----
1983 if (SOffset && Offset) { 0
1984 assert(!Imm32Only && !IsBuffer); 0
1985 SDValue B; 0
1986 return SelectSMRDBaseOffset(Addr, B, nullptr, Offset) && 0
1987 SelectSMRDBaseOffset(B, SBase, SOffset, nullptr); 0
1988 } ----
1989 ----
1990 // A 32-bit (address + offset) should not cause unsigned 32-bit integer ----
1991 // wraparound, because s_load instructions perform the addition in 64 bits. ----
1992 if (Addr.getValueType() == MVT::i32 && Addr.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD && 0
1993 !Addr->getFlags().hasNoUnsignedWrap()) 0
1994 return false; 0
1995 ----
1996 SDValue N0, N1; 0
1997 // Extract the base and offset if possible. ----
1998 if (CurDAG->isBaseWithConstantOffset(Addr) || Addr.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD) { 0
1999 N0 = Addr.getOperand(0); 0
2000 N1 = Addr.getOperand(1); 0
2001 } else if (getBaseWithOffsetUsingSplitOR(*CurDAG, Addr, N0, N1)) { 0
2002 assert(N0 && N1 && isa(N1)); 0
2003 } ----
2004 if (!N0 || !N1) 0
2005 return false; 0
2006 if (SelectSMRDOffset(N1, SOffset, Offset, Imm32Only, IsBuffer)) { 0
2007 SBase = N0; 0
2008 return true; 0
2009 } ----
2010 if (SelectSMRDOffset(N0, SOffset, Offset, Imm32Only, IsBuffer)) { 0
2011 SBase = N1; 0
2012 return true; 0
2013 } ----
2014 return false; 0
2015 } ----
2016 ----
2017 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectSMRD(SDValue Addr, SDValue &SBase, 0
2018 SDValue *SOffset, SDValue *Offset, ----
2019 bool Imm32Only) const { ----
2020 if (SelectSMRDBaseOffset(Addr, SBase, SOffset, Offset, Imm32Only)) { 0
2021 SBase = Expand32BitAddress(SBase); 0
2022 return true; 0
2023 } ----
2024 ----
2025 if (Addr.getValueType() == MVT::i32 && Offset && !SOffset) { 0
2026 SBase = Expand32BitAddress(Addr); 0
2027 *Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, SDLoc(Addr), MVT::i32); 0
2028 return true; 0
2029 } ----
2030 ----
2031 return false; 0
2032 } ----

2069 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectSMRDBufferSgprImm(SDValue N, SDValue &SOffset, 0
2070 SDValue &Offset) const { ----
2071 // Match the (soffset + offset) pair as a 32-bit register base and ----
2072 // an immediate offset. ----
2073 return N.getValueType() == MVT::i32 && 0
2074 SelectSMRDBaseOffset(N, /* SBase */ SOffset, /* SOffset*/ nullptr, 0

2078 ----
2079 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectMOVRELOffset(SDValue Index, 0
2080 SDValue &Base, ----
2081 SDValue &Offset) const { ----
2082 SDLoc DL(Index); 0
2083 ----
2084 if (CurDAG->isBaseWithConstantOffset(Index)) { 0
2085 SDValue N0 = Index.getOperand(0); 0
2086 SDValue N1 = Index.getOperand(1); 0
2087 ConstantSDNode *C1 = cast(N1); 0
2088 ----
2089 // (add n0, c0) ----
2090 // Don't peel off the offset (c0) if doing so could possibly lead ----
2091 // the base (n0) to be negative. ----
2092 // (or n0, |c0|) can never change a sign given isBaseWithConstantOffset. ----
2093 if (C1->getSExtValue() <= 0 || CurDAG->SignBitIsZero(N0) || 0
2094 (Index->getOpcode() == ISD::OR && C1->getSExtValue() >= 0)) { 0
2095 Base = N0; 0
2096 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(C1->getZExtValue(), DL, MVT::i32); 0
2097 return true; 0
2098 } ----
2099 } ----
2100 ----
2101 if (isa(Index)) 0
2102 return false; 0
2103 ----
2104 Base = Index; 0
2105 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
2106 return true; 0
2107 } 0
2108 ----
2109 SDNode *AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::getBFE32(bool IsSigned, const SDLoc &DL, 0
2110 SDValue Val, uint32_t Offset, ----
2111 uint32_t Width) { ----
2112 if (Val->isDivergent()) { 0
2113 unsigned Opcode = IsSigned ? AMDGPU::V_BFE_I32_e64 : AMDGPU::V_BFE_U32_e64; 0
2114 SDValue Off = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Offset, DL, MVT::i32); 0
2115 SDValue W = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Width, DL, MVT::i32); 0
2116 ----
2117 return CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opcode, DL, MVT::i32, Val, Off, W); 0
2118 } ----
2119 unsigned Opcode = IsSigned ? AMDGPU::S_BFE_I32 : AMDGPU::S_BFE_U32; 0
2120 // Transformation function, pack the offset and width of a BFE into ----
2121 // the format expected by the S_BFE_I32 / S_BFE_U32. In the second ----
2122 // source, bits [5:0] contain the offset and bits [22:16] the width. ----
2123 uint32_t PackedVal = Offset | (Width << 16); 0
2124 SDValue PackedConst = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(PackedVal, DL, MVT::i32); 0
2125 ----
2126 return CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opcode, DL, MVT::i32, Val, PackedConst); 0
2127 } ----
2128 ----
2129 void AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectS_BFEFromShifts(SDNode *N) { 0
2130 // "(a << b) srl c)" ---> "BFE_U32 a, (c-b), (32-c) ----
2131 // "(a << b) sra c)" ---> "BFE_I32 a, (c-b), (32-c) ----
2132 // Predicate: 0 < b <= c < 32 ----
2133 ----
2134 const SDValue &Shl = N->getOperand(0); 0
2135 ConstantSDNode *B = dyn_cast(Shl->getOperand(1)); 0
2136 ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(N->getOperand(1)); 0
2137 ----
2138 if (B && C) { 0
2139 uint32_t BVal = B->getZExtValue(); 0
2140 uint32_t CVal = C->getZExtValue(); 0
2141 ----
2142 if (0 < BVal && BVal <= CVal && CVal < 32) { 0
2143 bool Signed = N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRA; 0
2144 ReplaceNode(N, getBFE32(Signed, SDLoc(N), Shl.getOperand(0), CVal - BVal, 0
2145 32 - CVal)); ----
2146 return; 0
2147 } ----
2148 } ----
2149 SelectCode(N); 0
2150 } ----
2151 ----
2152 void AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectS_BFE(SDNode *N) { 0
2153 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
2154 case ISD::AND: 0
2155 if (N->getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::SRL) { 0
2156 // "(a srl b) & mask" ---> "BFE_U32 a, b, popcount(mask)" ----
2157 // Predicate: isMask(mask) ----
2158 const SDValue &Srl = N->getOperand(0); 0
2159 ConstantSDNode *Shift = dyn_cast(Srl.getOperand(1)); 0
2160 ConstantSDNode *Mask = dyn_cast(N->getOperand(1)); 0
2161 ----
2162 if (Shift && Mask) { 0
2163 uint32_t ShiftVal = Shift->getZExtValue(); 0
2164 uint32_t MaskVal = Mask->getZExtValue(); 0
2165 ----
2166 if (isMask_32(MaskVal)) { 0
2167 uint32_t WidthVal = llvm::popcount(MaskVal); 0
2168 ReplaceNode(N, getBFE32(false, SDLoc(N), Srl.getOperand(0), ShiftVal, 0
2169 WidthVal)); ----
2170 return; 0
2171 } ----
2172 } ----
2173 } ----
2174 break; 0
2175 case ISD::SRL: 0
2176 if (N->getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::AND) { 0
2177 // "(a & mask) srl b)" ---> "BFE_U32 a, b, popcount(mask >> b)" ----
2178 // Predicate: isMask(mask >> b) ----
2179 const SDValue &And = N->getOperand(0); 0
2180 ConstantSDNode *Shift = dyn_cast(N->getOperand(1)); 0
2181 ConstantSDNode *Mask = dyn_cast(And->getOperand(1)); 0
2182 ----
2183 if (Shift && Mask) { 0
2184 uint32_t ShiftVal = Shift->getZExtValue(); 0
2185 uint32_t MaskVal = Mask->getZExtValue() >> ShiftVal; 0
2186 ----
2187 if (isMask_32(MaskVal)) { 0
2188 uint32_t WidthVal = llvm::popcount(MaskVal); 0
2189 ReplaceNode(N, getBFE32(false, SDLoc(N), And.getOperand(0), ShiftVal, 0
2190 WidthVal)); ----
2191 return; 0
2192 } ----
2193 } ----
2194 } else if (N->getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) { 0
2195 SelectS_BFEFromShifts(N); 0
2196 return; 0
2197 } ----
2198 break; 0
2199 case ISD::SRA: 0
2200 if (N->getOperand(0).getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) { 0
2201 SelectS_BFEFromShifts(N); 0
2202 return; 0
2203 } ----
2204 break; 0
2205 ----
2206 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG: { 0
2207 // sext_inreg (srl x, 16), i8 -> bfe_i32 x, 16, 8 ----
2208 SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0); 0
2209 if (Src.getOpcode() != ISD::SRL) 0
2210 break; 0
2211 ----
2212 const ConstantSDNode *Amt = dyn_cast(Src.getOperand(1)); 0
2213 if (!Amt) 0
2214 break; 0
2215 ----
2216 unsigned Width = cast(N->getOperand(1))->getVT().getSizeInBits(); 0
2217 ReplaceNode(N, getBFE32(true, SDLoc(N), Src.getOperand(0), 0
2218 Amt->getZExtValue(), Width)); 0
2219 return; 0
2220 } ----
2221 } ----
2222 ----
2223 SelectCode(N); 0
2224 } ----
2225 ----
2226 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::isCBranchSCC(const SDNode *N) const { 0
2227 assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::BRCOND); 0
2228 if (!N->hasOneUse()) 0
2229 return false; 0
2230 ----
2231 SDValue Cond = N->getOperand(1); 0
2232 if (Cond.getOpcode() == ISD::CopyToReg) 0
2233 Cond = Cond.getOperand(2); 0
2234 ----
2235 if (Cond.getOpcode() != ISD::SETCC || !Cond.hasOneUse()) 0
2236 return false; 0
2237 ----
2238 MVT VT = Cond.getOperand(0).getSimpleValueType(); 0
2239 if (VT == MVT::i32) 0
2240 return true; 0
2241 ----
2242 if (VT == MVT::i64) { 0
2243 auto ST = static_cast(Subtarget); 0
2244 ----
2245 ISD::CondCode CC = cast(Cond.getOperand(2))->get(); 0
2246 return (CC == ISD::SETEQ || CC == ISD::SETNE) && ST->hasScalarCompareEq64(); 0
2247 } ----
2248 ----
2249 return false; 0
2250 } ----
2251 ----
2252 void AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectBRCOND(SDNode *N) { 0
2253 SDValue Cond = N->getOperand(1); 0
2254 ----
2255 if (Cond.isUndef()) { 0
2256 CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, AMDGPU::SI_BR_UNDEF, MVT::Other, 0
2257 N->getOperand(2), N->getOperand(0)); 0
2258 return; 0
2259 } ----
2260 ----
2261 const GCNSubtarget *ST = static_cast(Subtarget); 0
2262 const SIRegisterInfo *TRI = ST->getRegisterInfo(); 0
2263 ----
2264 bool UseSCCBr = isCBranchSCC(N) && isUniformBr(N); 0
2265 unsigned BrOp = UseSCCBr ? AMDGPU::S_CBRANCH_SCC1 : AMDGPU::S_CBRANCH_VCCNZ; 0
2266 Register CondReg = UseSCCBr ? AMDGPU::SCC : TRI->getVCC(); 0
2267 SDLoc SL(N); 0
2268 ----
2269 if (!UseSCCBr) { 0
2270 // This is the case that we are selecting to S_CBRANCH_VCCNZ. We have not ----
2271 // analyzed what generates the vcc value, so we do not know whether vcc ----
2272 // bits for disabled lanes are 0. Thus we need to mask out bits for ----
2273 // disabled lanes. ----
2274 // ----
2275 // For the case that we select S_CBRANCH_SCC1 and it gets ----
2276 // changed to S_CBRANCH_VCCNZ in SIFixSGPRCopies, SIFixSGPRCopies calls ----
2277 // SIInstrInfo::moveToVALU which inserts the S_AND). ----
2278 // ----
2279 // We could add an analysis of what generates the vcc value here and omit ----
2280 // the S_AND when is unnecessary. But it would be better to add a separate ----
2281 // pass after SIFixSGPRCopies to do the unnecessary S_AND removal, so it ----
2282 // catches both cases. ----
2283 Cond = SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode(ST->isWave32() ? AMDGPU::S_AND_B32 0
2284 : AMDGPU::S_AND_B64, ----
2285 SL, MVT::i1, ----
2286 CurDAG->getRegister(ST->isWave32() ? AMDGPU::EXEC_LO 0
2287 : AMDGPU::EXEC, ----
2288 MVT::i1), ----
2289 Cond), ----
2290 0); ----
2291 } ----
2292 ----
2293 SDValue VCC = CurDAG->getCopyToReg(N->getOperand(0), SL, CondReg, Cond); 0
2294 CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, BrOp, MVT::Other, 0
2295 N->getOperand(2), // Basic Block 0
2296 VCC.getValue(0)); ----
2297 } 0
