2299 void AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectDSAppendConsume(SDNode *N, unsigned IntrID) { 0
2300 // The address is assumed to be uniform, so if it ends up in a VGPR, it will ----
2301 // be copied to an SGPR with readfirstlane. ----
2302 unsigned Opc = IntrID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_ds_append ? 0
2303 AMDGPU::DS_APPEND : AMDGPU::DS_CONSUME; ----
2304 ----
2305 SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0); 0
2306 SDValue Ptr = N->getOperand(2); 0
2307 MemIntrinsicSDNode *M = cast(N); 0
2308 MachineMemOperand *MMO = M->getMemOperand(); 0
2309 bool IsGDS = M->getAddressSpace() == AMDGPUAS::REGION_ADDRESS; 0
2310 ----
2311 SDValue Offset; 0
2312 if (CurDAG->isBaseWithConstantOffset(Ptr)) { 0
2313 SDValue PtrBase = Ptr.getOperand(0); 0
2314 SDValue PtrOffset = Ptr.getOperand(1); 0
2315 ----
2316 const APInt &OffsetVal = cast(PtrOffset)->getAPIntValue(); 0
2317 if (isDSOffsetLegal(PtrBase, OffsetVal.getZExtValue())) { 0
2318 N = glueCopyToM0(N, PtrBase); 0
2319 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(OffsetVal, SDLoc(), MVT::i32); 0
2320 } ----
2321 } ----
2322 ----
2323 if (!Offset) { 0
2324 N = glueCopyToM0(N, Ptr); 0
2325 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, SDLoc(), MVT::i32); 0
2326 } ----
2327 ----
2328 SDValue Ops[] = { ----
2329 Offset, ----
2330 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(IsGDS, SDLoc(), MVT::i32), 0
2331 Chain, ----
2332 N->getOperand(N->getNumOperands() - 1) // New glue 0
2333 }; 0
2334 ----
2335 SDNode *Selected = CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, Opc, N->getVTList(), Ops); 0
2336 CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(cast(Selected), {MMO}); 0
2337 } 0

2343 SDValue Ops[] = {N->getOperand(2), N->getOperand(3), N->getOperand(4), 0
2344 N->getOperand(5), N->getOperand(0)}; 0
2345 ----

2347 MachineMemOperand *MMO = M->getMemOperand(); 0

2349 CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(cast(Selected), {MMO}); 0

2352 static unsigned gwsIntrinToOpcode(unsigned IntrID) { 0
2353 switch (IntrID) { 0
2354 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ds_gws_init: 0
2355 return AMDGPU::DS_GWS_INIT; 0
2356 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ds_gws_barrier: 0
2357 return AMDGPU::DS_GWS_BARRIER; 0
2358 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ds_gws_sema_v: 0
2359 return AMDGPU::DS_GWS_SEMA_V; 0
2360 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ds_gws_sema_br: 0
2361 return AMDGPU::DS_GWS_SEMA_BR; 0
2362 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ds_gws_sema_p: 0
2363 return AMDGPU::DS_GWS_SEMA_P; 0
2364 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ds_gws_sema_release_all: 0
2365 return AMDGPU::DS_GWS_SEMA_RELEASE_ALL; 0
2366 default: 0
2367 llvm_unreachable("not a gws intrinsic"); 0
2368 } ----
2369 } ----
2370 ----
2371 void AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectDS_GWS(SDNode *N, unsigned IntrID) { 0
2372 if (IntrID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_ds_gws_sema_release_all && 0
2373 !Subtarget->hasGWSSemaReleaseAll()) { 0
2374 // Let this error. ----
2375 SelectCode(N); 0
2376 return; 0
2377 } ----
2378 ----
2379 // Chain, intrinsic ID, vsrc, offset ----
2380 const bool HasVSrc = N->getNumOperands() == 4; 0
2381 assert(HasVSrc || N->getNumOperands() == 3); 0
2382 ----
2383 SDLoc SL(N); 0
2384 SDValue BaseOffset = N->getOperand(HasVSrc ? 3 : 2); 0
2385 int ImmOffset = 0; 0
2386 MemIntrinsicSDNode *M = cast(N); 0
2387 MachineMemOperand *MMO = M->getMemOperand(); 0
2388 ----
2389 // Don't worry if the offset ends up in a VGPR. Only one lane will have ----
2390 // effect, so SIFixSGPRCopies will validly insert readfirstlane. ----
2391 ----
2392 // The resource id offset is computed as ( + M0[21:16] + ----
2393 // offset field) % 64. Some versions of the programming guide omit the m0 ----
2394 // part, or claim it's from offset 0. ----
2395 if (ConstantSDNode *ConstOffset = dyn_cast(BaseOffset)) { 0
2396 // If we have a constant offset, try to use the 0 in m0 as the base. ----
2397 // TODO: Look into changing the default m0 initialization value. If the ----
2398 // default -1 only set the low 16-bits, we could leave it as-is and add 1 to ----
2399 // the immediate offset. ----
2400 glueCopyToM0(N, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, SL, MVT::i32)); 0
2401 ImmOffset = ConstOffset->getZExtValue(); 0
2402 } else { ----
2403 if (CurDAG->isBaseWithConstantOffset(BaseOffset)) { 0
2404 ImmOffset = BaseOffset.getConstantOperandVal(1); 0
2405 BaseOffset = BaseOffset.getOperand(0); 0
2406 } ----
2407 ----
2408 // Prefer to do the shift in an SGPR since it should be possible to use m0 ----
2409 // as the result directly. If it's already an SGPR, it will be eliminated ----
2410 // later. ----
2411 SDNode *SGPROffset ----
2412 = CurDAG->getMachineNode(AMDGPU::V_READFIRSTLANE_B32, SL, MVT::i32, 0
2413 BaseOffset); ----
2414 // Shift to offset in m0 ----
2415 SDNode *M0Base ----
2416 = CurDAG->getMachineNode(AMDGPU::S_LSHL_B32, SL, MVT::i32, 0
2417 SDValue(SGPROffset, 0), ----
2418 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(16, SL, MVT::i32)); 0
2419 glueCopyToM0(N, SDValue(M0Base, 0)); 0
2420 } ----
2421 ----
2422 SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0); 0
2423 SDValue OffsetField = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmOffset, SL, MVT::i32); 0
2424 ----
2425 const unsigned Opc = gwsIntrinToOpcode(IntrID); 0
2426 SmallVector Ops; 0
2427 if (HasVSrc) 0
2428 Ops.push_back(N->getOperand(2)); 0
2429 Ops.push_back(OffsetField); 0
2430 Ops.push_back(Chain); 0
2431 ----
2432 SDNode *Selected = CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, Opc, N->getVTList(), Ops); 0
2433 CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(cast(Selected), {MMO}); 0
2434 } 0

2436 void AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectInterpP1F16(SDNode *N) { 0
2437 if (Subtarget->getLDSBankCount() != 16) { 0
2438 // This is a single instruction with a pattern. ----
2439 SelectCode(N); 0
2440 return; 0
2441 } ----
2442 ----
2443 SDLoc DL(N); 0
2444 ----
2445 // This requires 2 instructions. It is possible to write a pattern to support ----
2446 // this, but the generated isel emitter doesn't correctly deal with multiple ----
2447 // output instructions using the same physical register input. The copy to m0 ----
2448 // is incorrectly placed before the second instruction. ----
2449 // ----
2450 // TODO: Match source modifiers. ----
2451 // ----
2452 // def : Pat < ----
2453 // (int_amdgcn_interp_p1_f16 ----
2454 // (VOP3Mods f32:$src0, i32:$src0_modifiers), ----
2455 // (i32 timm:$attrchan), (i32 timm:$attr), ----
2456 // (i1 timm:$high), M0), ----
2457 // (V_INTERP_P1LV_F16 $src0_modifiers, VGPR_32:$src0, timm:$attr, ----
2458 // timm:$attrchan, 0, ----
2459 // (V_INTERP_MOV_F32 2, timm:$attr, timm:$attrchan), timm:$high)> { ----
2460 // let Predicates = [has16BankLDS]; ----
2461 // } ----
2462 ----
2463 // 16 bank LDS ----
2464 SDValue ToM0 = CurDAG->getCopyToReg(CurDAG->getEntryNode(), DL, AMDGPU::M0, 0
2465 N->getOperand(5), SDValue()); 0
2466 ----
2467 SDVTList VTs = CurDAG->getVTList(MVT::f32, MVT::Other); 0
2468 ----
2469 SDNode *InterpMov = ----
2470 CurDAG->getMachineNode(AMDGPU::V_INTERP_MOV_F32, DL, VTs, { 0
2471 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(2, DL, MVT::i32), // P0 0
2472 N->getOperand(3), // Attr 0
2473 N->getOperand(2), // Attrchan 0
2474 ToM0.getValue(1) // In glue 0
2475 }); ----
2476 ----
2477 SDNode *InterpP1LV = ----
2478 CurDAG->getMachineNode(AMDGPU::V_INTERP_P1LV_F16, DL, MVT::f32, { 0
2479 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32), // $src0_modifiers 0
2480 N->getOperand(1), // Src0 0
2481 N->getOperand(3), // Attr 0
2482 N->getOperand(2), // Attrchan 0
2483 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32), // $src2_modifiers 0
2484 SDValue(InterpMov, 0), // Src2 - holds two f16 values selected by high ----
2485 N->getOperand(4), // high 0
2486 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i1), // $clamp 0
2487 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32), // $omod 0
2488 SDValue(InterpMov, 1) ----
2489 }); ----
2490 ----
2491 CurDAG->ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), SDValue(InterpP1LV, 0)); 0
2492 } 0

2571 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectVOP3ModsImpl(SDValue In, SDValue &Src, 0
2572 unsigned &Mods, ----
2573 bool IsCanonicalizing, ----
2574 bool AllowAbs) const { ----
2575 Mods = SISrcMods::NONE; 0
2576 Src = In; 0
2577 ----
2578 if (Src.getOpcode() == ISD::FNEG) { 0
2579 Mods |= SISrcMods::NEG; 0
2580 Src = Src.getOperand(0); 0
2581 } else if (Src.getOpcode() == ISD::FSUB && IsCanonicalizing) { 0
2582 // Fold fsub [+-]0 into fneg. This may not have folded depending on the ----
2583 // denormal mode, but we're implicitly canonicalizing in a source operand. ----
2584 auto *LHS = dyn_cast(Src.getOperand(0)); 0
2585 if (LHS && LHS->isZero()) { 0
2586 Mods |= SISrcMods::NEG; 0
2587 Src = Src.getOperand(1); 0
2588 } ----
2589 } ----
2590 ----
2591 if (AllowAbs && Src.getOpcode() == ISD::FABS) { 0
2592 Mods |= SISrcMods::ABS; 0
2593 Src = Src.getOperand(0); 0
2594 } ----
2595 ----
2596 return true; 0
2597 } ----

2602 if (SelectVOP3ModsImpl(In, Src, Mods, /*IsCanonicalizing=*/true, 0
2603 /*AllowAbs=*/true)) { ----
2604 SrcMods = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Mods, SDLoc(In), MVT::i32); 0
2605 return true; 0
2606 } ----
2607 ----
2608 return false; 0
2609 } ----

2701 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectVOP3PMods(SDValue In, SDValue &Src, 0
2702 SDValue &SrcMods, bool IsDOT) const { ----

2717 SDValue Hi = stripBitcast(Src.getOperand(1)); 0
2718 ----
2719 if (Lo.getOpcode() == ISD::FNEG) { 0

2723 ----
2724 if (Hi.getOpcode() == ISD::FNEG) { 0
2725 Hi = stripBitcast(Hi.getOperand(0)); 0
2726 Mods ^= SISrcMods::NEG_HI; 0

2728 ----
2729 if (isExtractHiElt(Lo, Lo)) 0

2731 ----
2732 if (isExtractHiElt(Hi, Hi)) 0
2733 Mods |= SISrcMods::OP_SEL_1; 0

2736 Lo = stripExtractLoElt(Lo); 0
2737 Hi = stripExtractLoElt(Hi); 0

2739 if (Lo.getValueSizeInBits() > VecSize) { 0

2741 (VecSize > 32) ? AMDGPU::sub0_sub1 : AMDGPU::sub0, SDLoc(In), 0
2742 MVT::getIntegerVT(VecSize), Lo); ----
2743 } ----
2744 ----
2745 if (Hi.getValueSizeInBits() > VecSize) { 0
2746 Hi = CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg( 0
2747 (VecSize > 32) ? AMDGPU::sub0_sub1 : AMDGPU::sub0, SDLoc(In), 0
2748 MVT::getIntegerVT(VecSize), Hi); ----
2749 } ----
2750 ----
2751 assert(Lo.getValueSizeInBits() <= VecSize && 0
2752 Hi.getValueSizeInBits() <= VecSize); ----
2753 ----
2754 if (Lo == Hi && !isInlineImmediate(Lo.getNode())) { 0
2755 // Really a scalar input. Just select from the low half of the register to ----
2756 // avoid packing. ----
2757 ----
2758 if (VecSize == 32 || VecSize == Lo.getValueSizeInBits()) { 0
2759 Src = Lo; 0
2760 } else { ----

2770 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RC, SL, MVT::i32), 0
2771 Lo, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub0, SL, MVT::i32), 0
2772 Undef, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub1, SL, MVT::i32) }; 0
2773 ----

2775 Src.getValueType(), Ops), 0); ----
2776 } 0
2777 SrcMods = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Mods, SDLoc(In), MVT::i32); 0

2779 } ----

2782 uint64_t Lit = cast(Lo)->getValueAPF() 0
2783 .bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue(); 0
2784 if (AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral32(Lit, Subtarget->hasInv2PiInlineImm())) { 0

2786 SrcMods = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Mods, SDLoc(In), MVT::i32); 0

2788 } ----
2789 } ----
2790 ----
2791 Mods = VecMods; 0
2792 } ----
2793 ----
2794 // Packed instructions do not have abs modifiers. ----
2795 Mods |= SISrcMods::OP_SEL_1; 0
2796 ----
2797 SrcMods = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Mods, SDLoc(In), MVT::i32); 0

2849 // The return value is not whether the match is possible (which it always is), ----
2850 // but whether or not it a conversion is really used. ----
2851 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::SelectVOP3PMadMixModsImpl(SDValue In, SDValue &Src, 0
2852 unsigned &Mods) const { ----
2853 Mods = 0; 0
2854 SelectVOP3ModsImpl(In, Src, Mods); 0
2855 ----
2856 if (Src.getOpcode() == ISD::FP_EXTEND) { 0
2857 Src = Src.getOperand(0); 0
2858 assert(Src.getValueType() == MVT::f16); 0
2859 Src = stripBitcast(Src); 0
2860 ----
2861 // Be careful about folding modifiers if we already have an abs. fneg is ----
2862 // applied last, so we don't want to apply an earlier fneg. ----
2863 if ((Mods & SISrcMods::ABS) == 0) { 0
2864 unsigned ModsTmp; ----
2865 SelectVOP3ModsImpl(Src, Src, ModsTmp); 0
2866 ----
2867 if ((ModsTmp & SISrcMods::NEG) != 0) 0
2868 Mods ^= SISrcMods::NEG; 0
2869 ----
2870 if ((ModsTmp & SISrcMods::ABS) != 0) 0
2871 Mods |= SISrcMods::ABS; 0
2872 } ----
2873 ----
2874 // op_sel/op_sel_hi decide the source type and source. ----
2875 // If the source's op_sel_hi is set, it indicates to do a conversion from fp16. ----
2876 // If the sources's op_sel is set, it picks the high half of the source ----
2877 // register. ----
2878 ----
2879 Mods |= SISrcMods::OP_SEL_1; 0
2880 if (isExtractHiElt(Src, Src)) { 0
2881 Mods |= SISrcMods::OP_SEL_0; 0
2882 ----
2883 // TODO: Should we try to look for neg/abs here? ----
2884 } ----
2885 ----
2886 return true; 0
2887 } ----
2888 ----
2889 return false; 0
2890 } ----

2931 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::isVGPRImm(const SDNode * N) const { 0
2932 assert(CurDAG->getTarget().getTargetTriple().getArch() == Triple::amdgcn); 0
2933 ----
2934 const SIRegisterInfo *SIRI = ----
2935 static_cast(Subtarget->getRegisterInfo()); 0
2936 const SIInstrInfo * SII = ----
2937 static_cast(Subtarget->getInstrInfo()); 0
2938 ----
2939 unsigned Limit = 0; 0
2940 bool AllUsesAcceptSReg = true; 0
2941 for (SDNode::use_iterator U = N->use_begin(), E = SDNode::use_end(); 0
2942 Limit < 10 && U != E; ++U, ++Limit) { 0
2943 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = getOperandRegClass(*U, U.getOperandNo()); 0
2944 ----
2945 // If the register class is unknown, it could be an unknown ----
2946 // register class that needs to be an SGPR, e.g. an inline asm ----
2947 // constraint ----
2948 if (!RC || SIRI->isSGPRClass(RC)) 0
2949 return false; 0
2950 ----
2951 if (RC != &AMDGPU::VS_32RegClass) { 0
2952 AllUsesAcceptSReg = false; 0
2953 SDNode * User = *U; 0
2954 if (User->isMachineOpcode()) { 0
2955 unsigned Opc = User->getMachineOpcode(); 0
2956 const MCInstrDesc &Desc = SII->get(Opc); 0
2957 if (Desc.isCommutable()) { 0
2958 unsigned OpIdx = Desc.getNumDefs() + U.getOperandNo(); 0
2959 unsigned CommuteIdx1 = TargetInstrInfo::CommuteAnyOperandIndex; 0
2960 if (SII->findCommutedOpIndices(Desc, OpIdx, CommuteIdx1)) { 0
2961 unsigned CommutedOpNo = CommuteIdx1 - Desc.getNumDefs(); 0
2962 const TargetRegisterClass *CommutedRC = getOperandRegClass(*U, CommutedOpNo); 0
2963 if (CommutedRC == &AMDGPU::VS_32RegClass) 0
2964 AllUsesAcceptSReg = true; 0
2965 } ----
2966 } ----
2967 } ----
2968 // If "AllUsesAcceptSReg == false" so far we haven't succeeded ----
2969 // commuting current user. This means have at least one use ----
2970 // that strictly require VGPR. Thus, we will not attempt to commute ----
2971 // other user instructions. ----
2972 if (!AllUsesAcceptSReg) 0
2973 break; 0
2974 } ----
2975 } ----
2976 return !AllUsesAcceptSReg && (Limit < 10); 0
2977 } ----
2978 ----
2979 bool AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::isUniformLoad(const SDNode * N) const { 0
2980 auto Ld = cast(N); 0
2981 ----
2982 if (N->isDivergent() && !AMDGPUInstrInfo::isUniformMMO(Ld->getMemOperand())) 0
2983 return false; 0
2984 ----
2985 return Ld->getAlign() >= Align(4) && 0
2986 ((Ld->getAddressSpace() == AMDGPUAS::CONSTANT_ADDRESS || 0
2987 Ld->getAddressSpace() == AMDGPUAS::CONSTANT_ADDRESS_32BIT) || 0
2988 (Subtarget->getScalarizeGlobalBehavior() && 0
2989 Ld->getAddressSpace() == AMDGPUAS::GLOBAL_ADDRESS && 0
2990 Ld->isSimple() && 0
2991 static_cast(getTargetLowering()) 0
2992 ->isMemOpHasNoClobberedMemOperand(N))); 0
2993 } ----

2995 void AMDGPUDAGToDAGISel::PostprocessISelDAG() { 0
2996 const AMDGPUTargetLowering& Lowering = ----
2997 *static_cast(getTargetLowering()); 0
2998 bool IsModified = false; 0
2999 do { 0
3000 IsModified = false; 0
3001 ----
3002 // Go over all selected nodes and try to fold them a bit more ----
3003 SelectionDAG::allnodes_iterator Position = CurDAG->allnodes_begin(); 0
3004 while (Position != CurDAG->allnodes_end()) { 0
3005 SDNode *Node = &*Position++; 0
3006 MachineSDNode *MachineNode = dyn_cast(Node); 0
3007 if (!MachineNode) 0
3008 continue; 0
3009 ----
3010 SDNode *ResNode = Lowering.PostISelFolding(MachineNode, *CurDAG); 0
3011 if (ResNode != Node) { 0
3012 if (ResNode) 0
3013 ReplaceUses(Node, ResNode); 0
3014 IsModified = true; 0
3015 } ----
3016 } ----
3017 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNodes(); 0
3018 } while (IsModified); ----
3019 } 0
